time, Capt. Sharma.

510
00:36:08,640 --> 00:36:10,890
- Please call me Shikha.
- Aparna.

511
00:36:12,970 --> 00:36:14,960
You have been posted here
just for my sake.

512
00:36:15,800 --> 00:36:17,040
I hope you are not
upset about that.

513
00:36:17,810 --> 00:36:18,760
Of course not.

514
00:36:19,320 --> 00:36:21,810
I got a chance to serve in SFTC
because of you.

515
00:36:23,090 --> 00:36:25,990
Anyway,
I wanted to meet that crazy girl...

516
00:36:26,620 --> 00:36:27,880
...who wants to be an example.

517
00:36:29,390 --> 00:36:30,340
No pressure.

518
00:36:30,840 --> 00:36:33,490
But the future of all the girls of
this country is in your hands.

519
00:36:35,860 --> 00:36:36,690
Thanks.

520
00:36:41,740 --> 00:36:42,640
Okay.

521
00:36:46,080 --> 00:36:47,890
Just some bruising.
No broken ribs.

522
00:36:49,490 --> 00:36:51,030
Okay.
Thank God.

523
00:36:51,110 --> 00:36:53,860
Or else, they'd have sent me back
before the course could even start.

524
00:36:54,430 --> 00:36:55,390
You can wear your shirt now.

525
00:37:03,780 --> 00:37:04,660
Tell me one thing.

526
00:37:06,020 --> 00:37:07,910
What were you thinking
when you went up there?

527
00:37:12,220 --> 00:37:13,710
[Gunshot]

528
00:37:23,340 --> 00:37:26,160
Actually, something similar
has happened before.

529
00:37:26,630 --> 00:37:28,860
And I couldn't do anything
at that time.

530
00:37:33,020 --> 00:37:34,000
Excuse me, ma'am.

531
00:37:34,810 --> 00:37:36,210
Colonel Sathe has called you.

532
00:37:53,450 --> 00:37:54,300
Afternoon, sir.

533
00:37:58,210 --> 00:38:02,210
You are trying to get on my nerves
from the very first day. Isn't it?

534
00:38:03,900 --> 00:38:05,310
Who gave you the permission
to go upstairs?

535
00:38:07,190 --> 00:38:09,960
Are you trained to handle such
situations, Capt. Sharma?

536
00:38:10,980 --> 00:38:12,290
Permission to speak freely, sir?

537
00:38:15,030 --> 00:38:16,190
Granted.
At ease.

538
00:38:18,130 --> 00:38:19,010
I'm very sorry, sir.

539
00:38:19,890 --> 00:38:23,180
I reacted with my instinct and gut
at the time of crisis, sir.

540
00:38:23,790 --> 00:38:25,060
But please correct If I'm wrong.

541
00:38:25,140 --> 00:38:27,150
But SF commandoes
are trained to do the same.

542
00:38:27,180 --> 00:38:29,240
You are not yet a
commando, Capt. Sharma.

543
00:38:31,080 --> 00:38:31,940
You are far from it.

544
00:38:34,060 --> 00:38:35,000
Do you even realise...

545
00:38:36,420 --> 00:38:39,160
...that I can throw
you out of the academy...

546
00:38:39,520 --> 00:38:41,140
...because of this behaviour
of yours?

547
00:38:45,280 --> 00:38:46,140
Yes, sir.

548
00:38:47,750 --> 00:38:49,920
But I won't do it.
It'll be too easy.

549
00:38:51,870 --> 00:38:53,350
I don't have to work
too hard for that.

550
00:38:54,160 --> 00:38:55,310
You will go on your own.

551
00:38:56,860 --> 00:38:58,260
You won't be able to
complete the course.

552
00:38:58,820 --> 00:39:00,140
I beg to differ, sir.

553
00:39:06,920 --> 00:39:09,070
You really think you are a
special case, don't you?

554
00:39:10,680 --> 00:39:11,520
No, sir.

555
00:39:12,480 --> 00:39:15,020
Then what?
A nutcase?

556
00:39:18,180 --> 00:39:22,160
- No, sir. - Then who the
hell do you think you are?

557
00:39:25,090 --> 00:39:27,150
The test case, sir.

558
00:39:49,040 --> 00:39:51,900
[Notification sound]

559
00:40:49,360 --> 00:40:54,160
[Theme music playing]

560
00:41:32,340 --> 00:41:33,940
- Good evening, sir.
- Good evening.

561
00:41:34,440 --> 00:41:35,680
My apologies, Capt. Sharma.

562
00:41:35,810 --> 00:41:37,830
Military Intelligence Directorate
has been on my a*s...

563
00:41:37,950 --> 00:41:39,000
...to take this from you.

564
00:41:39,400 --> 00:41:41,400
Sir, this will be my last job
for the MI.

565
00:41:42,430 --> 00:41:44,770
It has the intel
of the terrorist sleeper cell, sir.

566
00:41:45,320 --> 00:41:46,640
I hope you get the b******s, sir.

567
00:41:46,950 --> 00:41:47,860
I hope so too.

568
00:41:48,520 --> 00:41:50,110
Well, is your commander,
Colonel Sathe aware...

569
00:41:50,230 --> 00:41:52,060
...that you are here?
- Sir, had he known...

570
00:41:52,180 --> 00:41:55,160
...I would have been going home
by a Haryana Roadways bus.

571
00:41:55,260 --> 00:41:57,040
And if this was not
a time sensitive handover...

572
00:41:57,120 --> 00:42:00,930
...I wouldn't have risked jumping
the academy fence on the first day.

573
00:42:01,630 --> 00:42:04,460
If anyone deserves to be
the first woman in combat...

574
00:42:04,560 --> 00:42:05,970
...and in special forces...

575
00:42:06,060 --> 00:42:07,170
...it's definitely you.

576
00:42:07,360 --> 00:42:08,970
Thank you very much, sir.
Really good to see you.

577
00:42:09,050 --> 00:42:10,110
- Good to see you too.
- I'll take your leave.

578
00:42:10,200 --> 00:42:11,320
- Night, sir. Sir.
- Good night.

579
00:42:11,400 --> 00:42:13,400
[Engine starting]

580
00:42:28,120 --> 00:42:30,030
[Bhatti] 'Where the training
of the army ends...'

581
00:42:31,030 --> 00:42:33,280
[Bhatti] '...the training
of the special forces begins.

582
00:42:34,240 --> 00:42:37,040
Without sleep, water, or food...

583
00:42:37,840 --> 00:42:41,260
...you'll fight against
your enemy and win.

584
00:42:42,000 --> 00:42:43,330
From today, with every drill...

585
00:42:43,460 --> 00:42:45,790
...our leader board
will be updated.

586
00:42:46,950 --> 00:42:50,090
After 8 weeks, many officers
among you will pass out...

587
00:42:50,470 --> 00:42:52,270
...and become entitled
to the maroon beret.

588
00:42:52,360 --> 00:42:55,310
But only one of you,
who tops this course...

589
00:42:55,510 --> 00:42:57,690
...will get that special
commando dagger.

590
00:42:58,340 --> 00:43:00,330
- Did you get my point?
- Yes, sir...

591
00:43:00,710 --> 00:43:01,700
[Whistle]

592
00:43:03,580 --> 00:43:05,680
[Bhatti] 'Those who sweat
in peace...'

593
00:43:06,040 --> 00:43:07,950
[Bhatti] '...do not
shed blood in war.'

594
00:43:16,140 --> 00:43:18,480
[Bhatti] 'Your body will
get tired, you will lose hope...'

595
00:43:18,870 --> 00:43:21,000
[Bhatti] '...you will get
out of breath...'

596
00:43:21,470 --> 00:43:23,250
[Bhatti] '...but
you must not stop.'

597
00:43:34,300 --> 00:43:35,220
Speed up.

598
00:43:35,580 --> 00:43:37,250
Come on.
Hurry up...

599
00:43:37,370 --> 00:43:38,300
Hurry up...

600
00:43:43,180 --> 00:43:46,800
Hurry up...
This is special forces. Buck up!

601
00:44:26,180 --> 00:44:27,040
Jai Hind.

602
00:44:38,780 --> 00:44:39,680
Jai Hind, sir.

603
00:44:40,550 --> 00:44:41,440
Jai Hind, sir.

604
00:44:56,040 --> 00:44:58,420
The cut-off of this obstacle
was 7 minutes.

605
00:44:58,910 --> 00:45:02,730
Capt. Tank, you completed it
in 5 minutes and 7 seconds.

606
00:45:02,840 --> 00:45:03,970
Congratulations.

607
00:45:04,220 --> 00:45:05,760
You are in the first position.

608
00:45:06,870 --> 00:45:07,760
Capt. Manit.

609
00:45:08,180 --> 00:45:10,480
You are in the second position.
Very good.

610
00:45:12,840 --> 00:45:14,650
And Capt. Sharma,
what do we do with you?

611
00:45:15,550 --> 00:45:18,250
I think we have to make
a new obstacle course for you.

612
00:45:18,480 --> 00:45:20,500
- No, sir. I'll do it, sir.
- When?

613
00:45:22,460 --> 00:45:25,540
Your upper body strength
might be better than other girls.

614
00:45:25,660 --> 00:45:28,270
But special force training doesn't
differentiate between genders.

615
00:45:30,180 --> 00:45:32,990
Anyway, here in SFTC
there is a special principle.

616
00:45:34,550 --> 00:45:36,230
No matter who makes the mistake...

617
00:45:37,170 --> 00:45:38,300
...everybody gets punished.

618
00:45:40,010 --> 00:45:43,690
Until Capt. Sharma completes
this obstacle within 7 minutes...

619
00:45:44,170 --> 00:45:46,230
...everyone will get
limited ration.

620
00:45:47,500 --> 00:45:48,490
Lack of food.

621
00:45:49,950 --> 00:45:51,780
- Did you get it?
- Yes, sir...

622
00:45:52,930 --> 00:45:54,260
F*****g told you, man.

623
00:45:54,380 --> 00:45:56,100
All of us will be in trouble
because of her.

624
00:45:56,310 --> 00:45:57,190
Yes, dude.

625
00:45:57,270 --> 00:45:59,190
- Manit, S***e.
- Hey, Avinash.

626
00:45:59,270 --> 00:46:00,400
I am from the Garuds!

627
00:46:00,480 --> 00:46:01,760
What's up, my friend...

628
00:46:01,840 --> 00:46:04,330
- My friend. How are you?
- Very well.

629
00:46:04,410 --> 00:46:06,520
- You've impressed everyone here.
- Always, brother.

630
00:46:06,590 --> 00:46:07,820
Superb, man!

631
00:46:08,340 --> 00:46:12,000
By the way, have you met
the legendary Capt. Rathore?

632
00:46:12,080 --> 00:46:13,500
I met him in the mess,
very briefly.

633
00:46:13,630 --> 00:46:16,360
- Hi. - You hold a good reputation
in the regiment.

634
00:46:16,580 --> 00:46:18,770
- Good to finally meet you.
- Pleased to meet you.

635
00:46:20,510 --> 00:46:22,730
Rohan, your friend
is improving, dude.

636
00:46:24,230 --> 00:46:25,110
Shikha.

637
00:46:26,040 --> 00:46:27,950
I mean, Capt. Sharma.

638
00:46:29,310 --> 00:46:30,450
You too, man.

639
00:46:31,990 --> 00:46:33,470
You were together in NDA, right?

640
00:46:33,570 --> 00:46:36,960
Yes, we were.
People’s priorities change.

641
00:46:38,880 --> 00:46:42,490
- You okay?
- I hope this is not sympathy.

642
00:46:42,670 --> 00:46:44,680
Because that will make me
feel like an outsider.

643
00:46:44,770 --> 00:46:45,890
Not at all.

644
00:46:46,590 --> 00:46:47,580
It's...

645
00:46:47,930 --> 00:46:48,910
It's support.

646
00:46:50,130 --> 00:46:51,000
Believe me.

647
00:46:51,590 --> 00:46:53,600
I know what it feels like
to be an outsider.

648
00:46:54,210 --> 00:46:55,720
My name is Bilal Siddiqui.

649
00:46:56,880 --> 00:46:58,300
That is why I joined the army.

650
00:46:58,660 --> 00:47:00,920
Because here,
things just don't matter.

651
00:47:01,410 --> 00:47:02,320
Are you getting me?

652
00:47:05,010 --> 00:47:06,190
Call me Shikha, Bilal.

653
00:47:07,190 --> 00:47:08,060
I'll do that.

654
00:47:09,260 --> 00:47:10,160
See you.

655
00:47:10,250 --> 00:47:12,070
- See you at dinner. Bye.
- Sure.

656
00:47:16,450 --> 00:47:18,550
Read what is written on the wall.

657
00:47:18,940 --> 00:47:21,340
- We make men out of boys.
- We make men out of boys!

658
00:47:23,610 --> 00:47:24,610
What would I make out of you?

659
00:47:58,570 --> 00:48:01,760
I swear on Sunny Leone.
My stomach is growling.

660
00:48:02,780 --> 00:48:06,300
I am famished.
Lack of food is killing me.

661
00:48:09,060 --> 00:48:11,170
You have the solution
for your hunger.

662
00:48:11,380 --> 00:48:12,260
What?

663
00:48:12,360 --> 00:48:14,160
- Eat Ms. Savita.
- S***e.

664
00:48:14,690 --> 00:48:15,880
It sounds so wrong.

665
00:48:15,970 --> 00:48:17,180
Hey, come on.

666
00:48:17,500 --> 00:48:20,580
Banta, your Santa is here.
And look what I got.

667
00:48:20,670 --> 00:48:22,770
- Look.
- You thief! What is this?

668
00:48:22,860 --> 00:48:24,150
I convinced the guard.

669
00:48:24,240 --> 00:48:26,360
And Capt. Manit got food from CSD.

670
00:48:26,770 --> 00:48:28,750
One minute...
First, repeat after me.

671
00:48:28,850 --> 00:48:30,930
- I am from the Garuds.
- Say, my friend...

672
00:48:31,010 --> 00:48:32,620
- Ahead.
- Always ahead..

673
00:48:32,700 --> 00:48:34,150
- Ahead.
- Always ahead..

674
00:48:34,230 --> 00:48:36,950
- Victory to...
- India...

675
00:48:39,420 --> 00:48:40,730
Slowly.
Everyone will get it.

676
00:48:42,030 --> 00:48:43,300
Move..

677
00:48:46,540 --> 00:48:48,190
- Did you finish the food?
- Yes, Dad.

678
00:48:48,270 --> 00:48:49,170
Good girl.

679
00:48:49,550 --> 00:48:51,060
I told your mother...

680
00:48:51,530 --> 00:48:54,580
...that you won't do homework
on the weekends. Okay?

681
00:48:54,660 --> 00:48:56,740
-'Love you, Dad.'
- I love you too, baby.

682
00:48:56,830 --> 00:48:57,730
Bye.

683
00:48:57,820 --> 00:48:59,360
You've changed a lot
after marriage.

684
00:49:00,860 --> 00:49:01,780
No, dude.

685
00:49:03,850 --> 00:49:05,840
I think it’s becoming a dad
that changes you.

686
00:49:08,290 --> 00:49:09,310
You'll know it one day.

687
00:49:10,630 --> 00:49:13,330
Your entire focus is on your kid.

688
00:49:14,560 --> 00:49:16,650
I mean..
You become so protective.

689
00:49:17,040 --> 00:49:18,740
Even if there is a mosquito
in the room...

690
00:49:18,900 --> 00:49:21,360
...you will be worried
that it might bite your daughter.

691
00:49:22,410 --> 00:49:25,360
- Dad of the year 2017.
- No, dude.

692
00:49:26,570 --> 00:49:29,570
All the mosquitoes and flies
remind me of our dearest Bilal.

693
00:49:30,110 --> 00:49:32,250
- Were you winking at me?
- Were you eyeballing me?

694
00:49:32,340 --> 00:49:33,940
No, sir.
There was a fly, sir.

695
00:49:36,780 --> 00:49:38,600
By the way, where is Bilal?

696
00:49:40,140 --> 00:49:41,030
Where do you think?

697
00:49:44,990 --> 00:49:45,870
15.

698
00:49:47,500 --> 00:49:48,410
16.

699
00:49:51,120 --> 00:49:52,020
Hey.

700
00:49:54,910 --> 00:49:55,850
Hi.

701
00:49:56,470 --> 00:49:58,860
- Good evening.
- Good evening.

702
00:50:03,410 --> 00:50:06,100
I thought you could use
some reinforcements.

703
00:50:13,420 --> 00:50:14,310
Are you sure?

704
00:50:17,100 --> 00:50:18,100
Thank you.

705
00:50:19,030 --> 00:50:21,050
But I don't want
to break more rules.

706
00:50:22,100 --> 00:50:26,080
I see! So, you have
already broken a rule.

707
00:50:33,530 --> 00:50:35,910
- Can I ask you something?
- Sure.

708
00:50:37,340 --> 00:50:40,300
Why are you...
Why are you killing yourself?

709
00:50:43,580 --> 00:50:46,680
Bilal, if I don't complete
this obstacle course...

710
00:50:47,250 --> 00:50:50,000
...Bhatti will throw me
out of here...

711
00:50:50,090 --> 00:50:51,500
...saying,
"Carry on, Capt. Sharma."

712
00:50:54,250 --> 00:50:56,190
I have to give it everything.

713
00:50:57,940 --> 00:50:59,460
It's do or die, Bilal.

714
00:51:01,920 --> 00:51:05,120
Is it important to prove a point
always and every time?

715
00:51:06,640 --> 00:51:08,160
Always and every time.

716
00:51:08,800 --> 00:51:14,000
"The motive of my life
is to protect my country."

717
00:51:14,110 --> 00:51:18,730
"India is in my heart."

718
00:51:19,290 --> 00:51:24,400
"I am not weak
nor less than anyone."

719
00:51:24,510 --> 00:51:29,530
"I don't mind sacrificing my life."

720
00:51:29,650 --> 00:51:34,930
"I am proud to say
that the tricolour is my life."

721
00:51:35,020 --> 00:51:38,830
"India is in my heart."

722
00:51:40,170 --> 00:51:44,960
"India is in my heart."

723
00:51:45,150 --> 00:51:51,070
"India is in my heart."

724
00:52:04,800 --> 00:52:05,680
Check.

725
00:52:07,370 --> 00:52:08,460
I am hungry.

726
00:52:08,540 --> 00:52:10,940
Eating a few biscuits
doesn't help at all.

727
00:52:12,020 --> 00:52:13,080
No problem.

728
00:52:14,030 --> 00:52:15,250
It's a matter of one day.

729
00:52:15,520 --> 00:52:16,910
Tomorrow, she will fail again.

730
00:52:17,110 --> 00:52:18,300
There will be no more
food shortage.

731
00:52:19,610 --> 00:52:20,560
No, dude.

732
00:52:21,240 --> 00:52:22,350
She is strong.

733
00:52:22,590 --> 00:52:24,660
And I have a feeling
that she will do it.

734
00:52:25,570 --> 00:52:27,800
- Let's bet for Rs. 2,000.
- Sure.

735
00:52:27,910 --> 00:52:29,830
Even I am in.
She won't be able to do it.

736
00:52:29,920 --> 00:52:32,400
- Dude.
- She will do it.

737
00:52:32,570 --> 00:52:34,380
- Right?
- Let's see.

738
00:52:38,240 --> 00:52:40,950
You came here because of a
minister's direct recommendation

739
00:52:41,030 --> 00:52:43,020
This is a special privilege
by itself.

740
00:52:43,470 --> 00:52:45,390
Say hello to the Military Barbie.

741
00:52:46,560 --> 00:52:48,370
Girls cannot become
a commando in the army.

742
00:52:48,670 --> 00:52:49,780
No pressure.

743
00:52:50,010 --> 00:52:52,990
But the future of all the girls
of this country is in your hands.

744
00:52:53,060 --> 00:52:54,870
I don't have to work
too hard for it.

745
00:52:55,240 --> 00:52:56,570
You will leave willingly.

746
00:53:02,970 --> 00:53:04,110
Only 20 are left.

747
00:53:08,760 --> 00:53:09,720
Capt. Sharma.

748
00:53:10,340 --> 00:53:12,260
We are giving you
the last chance today.

749
00:53:12,620 --> 00:53:16,200
If you fail,
your exit form is ready.

750
00:53:18,160 --> 00:53:19,830
But this time, the difficulties
will be doubled.

751
00:53:20,460 --> 00:53:21,650
You will be carrying a load
of 10 kilograms...

752
00:53:21,730 --> 00:53:23,000
...from the start.

753
00:53:24,650 --> 00:53:26,470
Because the weak
have no place here.

754
00:53:28,050 --> 00:53:30,150
- Did you get it?
- Yes, sir.

755
00:53:30,960 --> 00:53:34,230
Dude, I think I'll lose my money.

756
00:53:34,670 --> 00:53:35,810
Keep Rs. 2,000 ready.

757
00:53:40,920 --> 00:53:41,780
[Whistle]

758
00:54:32,910 --> 00:54:33,960
Come on, Capt. Sharma.

759
00:54:35,130 --> 00:54:36,630
It's easy to go home.

760
00:54:36,850 --> 00:54:38,370
But do you want to go home?

761
00:54:45,290 --> 00:54:46,280
Try!

762
00:55:24,390 --> 00:55:26,580
Come on...

763
00:55:27,390 --> 00:55:28,920
You shouldn't stop.
Pull yourself.

764
00:55:41,640 --> 00:55:42,660
Jai Hind, sir.

765
00:55:46,750 --> 00:55:51,530
[Footsteps]

766
00:56:06,070 --> 00:56:06,940
Done.

767
00:56:13,610 --> 00:56:14,520
At ease.

768
00:56:16,170 --> 00:56:17,840
7 minutes and 10 seconds.

769
00:56:24,960 --> 00:56:28,360
But you completed this course
carrying a load of 10 kilograms.

770
00:56:28,760 --> 00:56:30,270
So, according to our principles...

771
00:56:30,400 --> 00:56:32,390
...you are given 20 seconds extra.

772
00:56:35,830 --> 00:56:37,240
And because of this...

773
00:56:37,480 --> 00:56:40,080
...you are safe from getting
disqualified by 10 seconds.

774
00:56:47,150 --> 00:56:48,160
Congratulations, Capt. Sharma.

775
00:56:48,800 --> 00:56:50,330
I think there is still time
for you to go home.

776
00:56:50,460 --> 00:56:51,400
Thank you, sir.

777
00:56:52,790 --> 00:56:53,900
Go and have food.

778
00:56:54,300 --> 00:56:56,090
The food is served for all of you.

779
00:56:58,080 --> 00:56:59,090
Well, no matter what we say...

780
00:56:59,510 --> 00:57:00,920
...but she has an X-factor.

781
00:57:01,580 --> 00:57:02,840
That is why she won the bet.

782
00:57:03,610 --> 00:57:06,420
- What say, hero?
- For sure. Well... For sure.

783
00:57:08,380 --> 00:57:09,510
Capt. Rathore.

784
00:57:09,870 --> 00:57:10,870
You lost the bet.

785
00:57:12,060 --> 00:57:12,930
Hand me the money.

786
00:57:13,010 --> 00:57:14,960
Are we allowed to get wallet here?
I'll give it to you in the dorm.

787
00:57:15,040 --> 00:57:17,290
- Good evening, boys.
- Good evening.

788
00:57:17,480 --> 00:57:19,870
I heard about a bet...

789
00:57:19,990 --> 00:57:22,120
...that I won't be able
to complete the obstacle course.

790
00:57:22,540 --> 00:57:24,620
It's between the boys
so I don't want to interfere.

791
00:57:24,700 --> 00:57:26,720
But I feel bad
for the ones who lost.

792
00:57:26,840 --> 00:57:28,530
Just cut the crap, Capt. Sharma.
All right?

793
00:57:30,350 --> 00:57:32,820
Capt. Rathore.
Listen to what she has to say.

794
00:57:33,780 --> 00:57:35,320
Dude...
No offence to anyone.

795
00:57:35,460 --> 00:57:38,760
But I just want to say
that people should stay focused.

796
00:57:38,980 --> 00:57:41,860
Focus on the leader board.
Forget about betting.

797
00:57:42,950 --> 00:57:43,950
- Isn't it?
- Of course.

798
00:57:45,220 --> 00:57:46,430
- Won't you get me a beer?
- Of course.

799
00:57:46,510 --> 00:57:48,180
- I made you win.
- Come on.

800
00:57:49,220 --> 00:57:50,670
- Come on.
- Bilal, you coming?

801
00:57:50,760 --> 00:57:51,810
You'll be paying the bill.

802
00:57:53,890 --> 00:57:54,900
Come...

803
00:57:57,680 --> 00:57:58,570
Sir.

804
00:57:59,230 --> 00:58:02,290
Bar brawl with the police.
Right?

805
00:58:06,590 --> 00:58:08,210
Got any explanations?

806
00:58:08,290 --> 00:58:09,900
Sir, I was in Mhow.

807
00:58:10,370 --> 00:58:11,760
I had completed
the Junior Command Course.

808
00:58:13,680 --> 00:58:15,080
They were goons from Meerut.

809
00:58:16,400 --> 00:58:17,930
They were teasing my friend.
So, I..

810
00:58:18,460 --> 00:58:19,320
I just gave it back.

811
00:58:19,400 --> 00:58:21,720
But what do I do
about the FIR, Capt. Avinash?

812
00:58:30,910 --> 00:58:31,800
Look.

813
00:58:33,360 --> 00:58:34,780
Maybe everyone does...

814
00:58:35,520 --> 00:58:37,060
...what you did.

815
00:58:37,330 --> 00:58:40,220
But this is SFTC.
And we go by rules.

816
00:58:40,310 --> 00:58:43,570
I can't have someone in the academy
who has a police case on him.

817
00:58:46,640 --> 00:58:48,470
Finish your court case.

818
00:58:48,910 --> 00:58:50,710
And volunteer next year once again.

819
00:58:51,410 --> 00:58:55,110
Sir, please.
Reconsider it.

820
00:58:55,230 --> 00:58:57,470
Rules are rules, Capt. Avinash.

821
00:58:58,150 --> 00:58:59,430
- Sir...
- All the best.

822
00:59:03,810 --> 00:59:04,750
Dismissed.

823
00:59:09,170 --> 00:59:10,550
One more thing, Capt. Avinash.

824
00:59:13,700 --> 00:59:15,110
During the punishment
of lack of food...

825
00:59:16,480 --> 00:59:19,690
...food items from CSD canteen
were taken to the dorm.

826
00:59:20,820 --> 00:59:21,780
Am I right?

827
00:59:23,430 --> 00:59:26,520
- Yes.
- We are watching, always.

828
00:59:27,720 --> 00:59:30,510
While leaving, explain this
to your course mates.

829
00:59:35,910 --> 00:59:37,690
[Ranjit] 'Who must have
named him Tank?'

830
00:59:38,510 --> 00:59:41,230
- I heard his name is Tankesh.
- Tankesh?

831
00:59:43,420 --> 00:59:44,610
I prefer Tankinder.

832
00:59:46,270 --> 00:59:47,470
But he is good.

833
00:59:47,810 --> 00:59:49,330
He remains silent
when everybody laughs.

834
00:59:49,470 --> 00:59:50,780
And when everyone cries,
he laughs.

835
00:59:51,610 --> 00:59:53,410
Dude, I am feeling bad for Avinash.

836
00:59:53,700 --> 00:59:55,820
He was a good lad.
He had to leave for no reason.

837
00:59:55,910 --> 00:59:57,680
He always gets into trouble.

838
00:59:58,770 --> 01:00:01,370
I think that Military Barbie
is behind this.

839
01:00:02,270 --> 01:00:03,600
Military Barbie.

840
01:00:04,820 --> 01:00:06,810
We successfully maintained
our first week's record.

841
01:00:08,940 --> 01:00:10,880
Four have signed exit forms.

842
01:00:13,110 --> 01:00:15,720
- But she is still here.
- Yes, sir.

843
01:00:17,420 --> 01:00:19,410
We have underestimated her.

844
01:00:20,660 --> 01:00:22,480
She trained herself every night.

845
01:00:22,880 --> 01:00:24,900
And completed
the obstacle course today.

846
01:00:28,630 --> 01:00:32,550
- Sir, I wanted to ask something.
- Yes.

847
01:00:33,530 --> 01:00:35,460
Do we have to be
so strict with her?

848
01:00:43,660 --> 01:00:46,130
Mr. Bhatti, how long have you
been posted in SFTC?

849
01:00:47,740 --> 01:00:48,700
Eight years, sir.

850
01:00:48,810 --> 01:00:51,440
But you never asked me
this question in 8 years.

851
01:00:51,590 --> 01:00:52,920
Regarding another officer.

852
01:01:01,940 --> 01:01:02,930
One more thing.

853
01:01:12,870 --> 01:01:15,190
Capt. Shikha Sharma
had requested...

854
01:01:15,350 --> 01:01:17,560
...not to be given
any special treatment.

855
01:01:18,520 --> 01:01:21,240
But this has never happened, sir.

856
01:01:22,840 --> 01:01:26,380
That is because
a lady officer never applied...

857
01:01:26,460 --> 01:01:29,190
...to become
a special forces commando.

858
01:01:36,800 --> 01:01:37,680
F**k.

859
01:02:04,940 --> 01:02:05,920
What kind of a joke is this?

860
01:02:07,340 --> 01:02:08,720
Colonel Sathe's orders.

861
01:02:09,110 --> 01:02:11,120
I just have to find myself
a bed now.

862
01:02:11,470 --> 01:02:12,480
Welcome, Shikha.

863
01:02:13,140 --> 01:02:14,350
By the way, we have a rule here.

864
01:02:15,050 --> 01:02:17,630
You'll have to compete
with the heavy drinker here...

865
01:02:17,760 --> 01:02:18,870
...in order to get a bed.

866
01:02:24,430 --> 01:02:26,450
Who is that?

867
01:02:31,170 --> 01:02:32,030
I am.

868
01:02:36,300 --> 01:02:37,190
Okay.

869
01:02:37,280 --> 01:02:39,190
Come on...

870
01:02:40,100 --> 01:02:41,400
Well done.
Wonderful.

871
01:02:44,180 --> 01:02:45,090
Come on, Shikha.

872
01:02:45,790 --> 01:02:47,000
Come on, Rohan.

873
01:02:47,130 --> 01:02:48,920
[Applauding and cheering]

874
01:02:51,290 --> 01:02:52,880
You must not stop.

875
01:02:53,630 --> 01:02:55,940
Wow!
Look at his style. Wow.

876
01:02:56,390 --> 01:02:57,380
Wonderful!

877
01:02:57,920 --> 01:02:59,520
Come on...

878
01:02:59,630 --> 01:03:02,320
- Finish this.
- Rohan, come on!

879
01:03:12,220 --> 01:03:13,500
Dude!

880
01:03:13,540 --> 01:03:14,730
Come on, Shikha.
Come on.

881
01:03:14,810 --> 01:03:17,410
How much will you drink
to prove a point?

882
01:03:21,930 --> 01:03:23,540
Let it be, Capt. Sharma.

883
01:03:24,330 --> 01:03:27,450
Anyway, only men and horses
can digest rum.

884
01:03:29,670 --> 01:03:32,310
Where are the horses that drink rum?

885
01:03:32,850 --> 01:03:34,570
- Wonderful!
- Point.

886
01:03:35,270 --> 01:03:37,280
He was the only heavy drinker here
but now she has arrived.

887
01:03:37,750 --> 01:03:38,620
Hey!

888
01:03:38,970 --> 01:03:41,560
And I am saying this to you
with due respect, ma'am.

889
01:03:42,450 --> 01:03:44,650
Okay.
Come on, Surje.

890
01:03:47,210 --> 01:03:49,150
- Very good!
- Come on...

891
01:03:49,230 --> 01:03:51,450
[Cheering]

892
01:03:54,530 --> 01:03:55,550
Go, Rohan.

893
01:03:57,100 --> 01:04:00,140
I think Capt. Sharma
is about to give up.

894
01:04:00,540 --> 01:04:02,120
The game has just begun.

895
01:04:02,940 --> 01:04:05,250
Capt. Sharma, come on.
You can do this.

896
01:04:06,670 --> 01:04:07,550
[Man] Come on.

897
01:04:08,430 --> 01:04:11,140
Come on, Shikha.
Come on...

898
01:04:11,210 --> 01:04:13,440
[Applauding and cheering]

899
01:04:13,900 --> 01:04:14,760
Come on...

900
01:04:14,850 --> 01:04:16,560
- Come on...
- Well done...

901
01:04:16,650 --> 01:04:18,200
Come on...

902
01:04:18,290 --> 01:04:19,180
Shikha!

903
01:04:25,810 --> 01:04:27,530
[Bilal] Hey. Here.
Have some water.

904
01:04:28,120 --> 01:04:32,670
As the saying goes,
a single blow of a blacksmith...

905
01:04:32,760 --> 01:04:34,290
Is equivalent to a hundred blows
of a goldsmith...

906
01:04:37,040 --> 01:04:40,390
- I am impressed, Rohan.
- Let's go...

907
01:04:41,390 --> 01:04:42,410
Hey...

908
01:04:46,090 --> 01:04:48,080
To the floor, Barbie.

909
01:04:50,450 --> 01:04:51,860
Aye aye, Captain!

910
01:04:53,580 --> 01:04:57,020
Cheers, boys.
Capt. Sharma has lost the battle.

911
01:04:57,110 --> 01:04:59,290
[Cheering]

912
01:05:32,040 --> 01:05:34,030
I think you had too much
last night.

913
01:05:50,360 --> 01:05:51,490
As all of you know...

914
01:05:51,590 --> 01:05:53,260
...the Krav Maga of the Israelis...

915
01:05:53,890 --> 01:05:56,100
...is one of the best
martial art forms in the world.

916
01:05:56,850 --> 01:05:58,030
In the special forces...

917
01:05:58,210 --> 01:05:59,830
...hand to hand combat...

918
01:06:00,360 --> 01:06:01,560
...is more important than weapons.

919
01:06:16,120 --> 01:06:17,310
Capt. Rohan Rathore.

920
01:06:17,950 --> 01:06:21,060
Brigade of the Guards,
IMA, NDA.

921
01:06:21,420 --> 01:06:23,840
- Do you remember their rule?
- Yes, sir.

922
01:06:24,270 --> 01:06:27,130
Then, take 20 rounds.
Buddy piggyback.

923
01:06:27,850 --> 01:06:29,360
Everything will be all right.

924
01:06:33,270 --> 01:06:35,340
As per the rules
of special forces...

925
01:06:35,490 --> 01:06:37,290
...the commandos holding alternate
positions on the leader board...

926
01:06:37,370 --> 01:06:38,640
...are buddies.

927
01:06:40,890 --> 01:06:42,990
So according to that...
Capt. Manit!

928
01:06:44,560 --> 01:06:46,580
- You are Capt. Rohan's buddy.
- Yes, sir.

929
01:06:46,710 --> 01:06:49,120
Come on.
Fulfil your responsibility.

930
01:06:56,840 --> 01:06:59,240
Rathore, don't we look like
Vikram and Betal?

931
01:06:59,770 --> 01:07:01,300
F**k your PJs man, Manit.

932
01:07:01,430 --> 01:07:02,650
My head is aching.

933
01:07:02,730 --> 01:07:04,820
"You broke your silence,
so I'll fly away now."

934
01:07:06,420 --> 01:07:08,740
Are you done
or do you have more to say?

935
01:07:08,940 --> 01:07:11,020
There is more.
Eight more rounds to go.

936
01:07:11,320 --> 01:07:12,870
Who asked you to show off?

937
01:07:13,080 --> 01:07:14,470
You drank
one and a half bottle of liquor.

938
01:07:14,770 --> 01:07:16,360
I wanted to show her, her place.

939
01:07:16,440 --> 01:07:18,360
Yeah. But she showed you,
your place instead.

940
01:07:18,460 --> 01:07:19,560
What the f**k are you
talking about?

941
01:07:19,640 --> 01:07:21,470
- Don't you see what everyone can?
- What?

942
01:07:21,570 --> 01:07:23,080
She played you, partner.

943
01:07:24,270 --> 01:07:26,210
She laid a trap
and you fell into it.

944
01:07:26,840 --> 01:07:28,950
Capt. Rathore,
are you tired already?

945
01:07:29,240 --> 01:07:30,740
You shouldn't stop.
Come on, continue.

946
01:07:34,230 --> 01:07:36,930
[Woman] "As per our sources,
a lady officer has been sent..."

947
01:07:37,010 --> 01:07:40,010
"...for a commando course
in the special forces."

948
01:07:40,190 --> 01:07:41,920
"And her performance..."

949
01:07:42,010 --> 01:07:43,710
"...has left everyone speechless."

950
01:07:43,770 --> 01:07:47,280
"After the Test Case,
the defence minister is sure..."

951
01:07:54,410 --> 01:07:59,220
[Phone ringing and vibration]

952
01:08:05,200 --> 01:08:06,790
- Good morning, sir.
- Morning, Colonel.

953
01:08:07,510 --> 01:08:09,520
You must have heard
the breaking news.

954
01:08:09,700 --> 01:08:11,210
Apparently you and I
are speechless...

955
01:08:11,330 --> 01:08:14,030
...after seeing
Shikha Sharma's performance.

956
01:08:14,740 --> 01:08:16,760
[Bedi] 'Anyway, how is she doing?'

957
01:08:18,170 --> 01:08:21,100
In physical strength, the male
officers are better than her.

958
01:08:21,360 --> 01:08:23,690
But in shooting,
Capt. Sharma is quite strong.

959
01:08:24,120 --> 01:08:25,120
[Sathe] 'She thinks calmly.'

960
01:08:25,510 --> 01:08:28,510
After failing in the obstacle task,
she has come back really strong.

961
01:08:28,920 --> 01:08:32,340
You are praising her,
Colonel Sathe.

962
01:08:33,250 --> 01:08:36,570
General Bedi,
you know me very well.

963
01:08:37,100 --> 01:08:39,010
I won't praise anyone
without any reason.

964
01:08:39,290 --> 01:08:40,810
And I won't criticise her...

965
01:08:40,880 --> 01:08:42,180
...just because she
is a lady officer.

966
01:08:42,630 --> 01:08:44,050
[Sathe] 'I am just
telling you the facts.'

967
01:08:44,570 --> 01:08:47,290
The areas in which
most women would give up...

968
01:08:47,520 --> 01:08:49,850
...she is doing much better
than what I expected.

969
01:08:50,860 --> 01:08:51,750
[Sathe] 'However, sir.'

970
01:08:51,840 --> 01:08:54,560
From next week, strategy and
tactics training is going to start.

971
01:08:54,740 --> 01:08:55,950
Under Freddie, right?

972
01:08:56,020 --> 01:08:56,900
Yes, sir.

973
01:08:56,980 --> 01:08:58,510
Under Colonel Freddie Punawala.

974
01:08:58,970 --> 01:09:01,580
[Sathe] 'You know that not
everyone can do this.'

975
01:09:01,720 --> 01:09:03,710
Also Camp Dozakh is pending.

976
01:09:04,380 --> 01:09:05,990
She might clear
the tactics course...

977
01:09:06,090 --> 01:09:07,670
...but it won't be possible
for her...

978
01:09:08,590 --> 01:09:09,900
...to clear Dozakh.

979
01:09:10,520 --> 01:09:11,440
Are you sure?

980
01:09:13,330 --> 01:09:16,540
The failure rate of male officers
is 40 percent, sir.

981
01:09:17,940 --> 01:09:18,820
Remember, Colonel.

982
01:09:18,910 --> 01:09:20,900
This is not just
about Shikha Sharma.

983
01:09:21,550 --> 01:09:23,650
This is about the future
of the army.

984
01:09:25,010 --> 01:09:29,240
I just want our benchmark
to be the same.

985
01:09:29,580 --> 01:09:30,700
[Bedi] 'You know what I am saying.'

986
01:09:31,170 --> 01:09:32,250
Push her the hardest.

987
01:09:32,380 --> 01:09:33,250
Yes, sir.

988
01:09:44,000 --> 01:09:46,620
"I am used to winning."

989
01:09:46,700 --> 01:09:49,210
"This is the end of enemies."

990
01:09:49,330 --> 01:09:54,130
"India is in my heart."

991
01:09:54,420 --> 01:09:59,630
"The motive of my life
is to protect my country."

992
01:09:59,750 --> 01:10:04,620
"India is in my heart."

993
01:10:04,880 --> 01:10:09,990
"I am not weak
nor less than anyone."

994
01:10:10,150 --> 01:10:15,020
"I don't mind sacrificing my life."

995
01:10:15,250 --> 01:10:20,450
"I am proud to say
that tricolour is my life."

996
01:10:20,560 --> 01:10:24,460
"India is in my heart."

997
01:10:25,680 --> 01:10:30,070
"India is in my heart."

998
01:10:30,760 --> 01:10:35,460
"India is in my heart."

999
01:10:35,590 --> 01:10:38,700
Come on, Commandos.
Come on.

1000
01:11:13,900 --> 01:11:15,020
Well done, Officers!

1001
01:11:15,840 --> 01:11:16,710
Capt. Manit.

1002
01:11:17,430 --> 01:11:18,650
Because of your good performance...

1003
01:11:18,740 --> 01:11:20,060
...you are moving up
on the leader board.

1004
01:11:22,120 --> 01:11:23,050
Capt. Rohan.

1005
01:11:23,310 --> 01:11:25,770
Being disciplined is also important
apart from good performance...

1006
01:11:25,860 --> 01:11:27,280
...for the leader board positions.

1007
01:11:28,750 --> 01:11:31,680
Capt. Sharma,
keep up the good work.

1008
01:11:32,830 --> 01:11:34,020
That's all for today.

1009
01:11:34,950 --> 01:11:37,660
Good news comes without warning
in the special forces.

1010
01:11:38,500 --> 01:11:40,910
You can go anywhere you want
for six hours this evening.

1011
01:11:41,040 --> 01:11:42,430
You can do what you want.

1012
01:11:42,870 --> 01:11:44,240
But tomorrow morning at 5...

1013
01:11:44,330 --> 01:11:45,550
...be ready for the fall in.

1014
01:11:46,590 --> 01:11:48,180
Okay.
Dismissed.

1015
01:11:55,440 --> 01:11:57,240
Guys, hurry up.

1016
01:12:02,030 --> 01:12:03,650
[Door knocking]

1017
01:12:07,730 --> 01:12:09,630
How will you manage today,
Capt. Shikha?

1018
01:12:10,610 --> 01:12:12,290
The bus will leave in 15 minutes.

1019
01:12:12,790 --> 01:12:13,680
