Chemical warfare.

1275
01:29:36,100 --> 01:29:39,890
[Footsteps]

1276
01:29:40,020 --> 01:29:41,620
[Door opening]

1277
01:29:42,640 --> 01:29:43,770
[Bhatti] You will find
chlorobenzylidene malononitrile...

1278
01:29:43,850 --> 01:29:45,510
[Bhatti] ...inside the building.

1279
01:29:46,300 --> 01:29:48,400
[Bhatti] In short,
it is called CS gas.

1280
01:29:50,730 --> 01:29:53,040
[Bhatti] Even the American army
use this in their training.

1281
01:29:57,600 --> 01:29:59,610
[Bhatti] You will perform
this task with your buddy.

1282
01:30:01,010 --> 01:30:01,940
[Bhatti] Remember one thing.

1283
01:30:02,130 --> 01:30:04,380
[Bhatti] If you don't complete
this task in 2 minutes...

1284
01:30:04,850 --> 01:30:07,030
[Bhatti] ...your buddy
might lose his life.

1285
01:30:11,830 --> 01:30:13,270
[Bhatti] You will get to know
the value of every breath...

1286
01:30:13,350 --> 01:30:14,970
[Bhatti] ...while doing this task.

1287
01:30:18,200 --> 01:30:21,290
[Coughing]

1288
01:30:21,440 --> 01:30:23,500
[Bhatti] Both the buddies
will have to breath carefully.

1289
01:30:24,300 --> 01:30:25,800
[Bhatti] If you
inhale more oxygen...

1290
01:30:26,210 --> 01:30:28,590
[Bhatti] ...your buddy might not
get enough oxygen to breathe.

1291
01:30:28,700 --> 01:30:31,310
You can at least share the oxygen.

1292
01:30:41,370 --> 01:30:43,490
[Bhatti] If the oxygen gets over
before the task ends...

1293
01:30:44,700 --> 01:30:45,880
[Bhatti] ...you'll fail the test.

1294
01:30:47,490 --> 01:30:48,410
Get up.

1295
01:30:49,110 --> 01:30:51,590
- Get up.
- God!

1296
01:30:52,750 --> 01:30:53,860
Rohan.
Buddy.

1297
01:30:54,500 --> 01:30:55,430
Are you all right?

1298
01:30:56,950 --> 01:30:59,830
Rohan, are you all right?
What is happening?

1299
01:31:01,360 --> 01:31:03,940
Rohan, what is happening?

1300
01:31:06,350 --> 01:31:09,210
Rohan, don't fall.
Are you all right?

1301
01:31:10,500 --> 01:31:11,840
We need help.
Guys!

1302
01:31:12,870 --> 01:31:13,740
Guy...

1303
01:31:14,420 --> 01:31:15,340
Rohan.

1304
01:31:16,130 --> 01:31:17,870
Are you all right, Rohan?
What happened, Rohan?

1305
01:31:19,710 --> 01:31:23,800
Rohan...
No...

1306
01:31:25,230 --> 01:31:27,750
Rohan...
Rohan!

1307
01:31:31,230 --> 01:31:32,240
Rohan...

1308
01:31:32,460 --> 01:31:33,390
Rohan.

1309
01:31:36,260 --> 01:31:37,140
Rohan...

1310
01:31:40,240 --> 01:31:42,860
Get up.
Get up, Rohan...

1311
01:31:43,550 --> 01:31:45,480
Rohan...

1312
01:31:48,680 --> 01:31:50,350
[Coughing]

1313
01:31:59,130 --> 01:32:00,030
F**k!

1314
01:32:03,810 --> 01:32:05,130
Sorry, man. Manit.

1315
01:32:05,600 --> 01:32:07,310
S***e, had something happened
to you or me today...

1316
01:32:07,390 --> 01:32:08,710
...because
of your claustrophobia...

1317
01:32:08,780 --> 01:32:10,310
...even your dad wouldn't
have been able to do anything.

1318
01:32:11,480 --> 01:32:13,410
F**k, dude.
B******d.

1319
01:32:13,500 --> 01:32:15,160
[Coughing]

1320
01:32:22,550 --> 01:32:23,670
Are you all right, buddy?

1321
01:32:24,940 --> 01:32:28,140
Thanks, Bilal.
I have my own buddy.

1322
01:32:37,960 --> 01:32:40,340
We first need to win the battle
within, Capt. Rohan.

1323
01:32:40,700 --> 01:32:41,590
Got it?

1324
01:32:42,210 --> 01:32:44,130
In this way you will put
yourself, your buddy...

1325
01:32:44,210 --> 01:32:45,730
...and the entire unit in danger.

1326
01:32:45,870 --> 01:32:47,880
Give up your dream
of becoming a commando.

1327
01:32:49,980 --> 01:32:52,960
Listen, dear. I know
this was your father's dream.

1328
01:32:53,040 --> 01:32:55,060
This isn't dad's dream.
This is my dream.

1329
01:32:56,080 --> 01:32:57,850
I wanted Udit to fulfil
this dream of mine.

1330
01:32:57,950 --> 01:33:00,040
But I know what
brother went through.

1331
01:33:00,160 --> 01:33:01,190
Dad, you have no idea.

1332
01:33:02,940 --> 01:33:05,520
Brother never wanted
to join the army.

1333
01:33:05,690 --> 01:33:07,490
You always forced him.

1334
01:33:08,240 --> 01:33:09,450
Now that I want to join the army...

1335
01:33:09,530 --> 01:33:11,330
...you are trying to stop me.

1336
01:33:12,150 --> 01:33:15,210
We all saw the impact
of your stubbornness on brother.

1337
01:33:18,370 --> 01:33:20,790
- Now, don't try the same
thing on me. - Shikha!

1338
01:33:22,390 --> 01:33:25,500
What type of girl are you?
Don't you want to get married?

1339
01:33:26,910 --> 01:33:29,730
And we're ready to let you
marry the guy you like.

1340
01:33:31,890 --> 01:33:33,040
- And you!
- Yes.

1341
01:33:34,150 --> 01:33:36,540
- Will you marry her?
- Yes.

1342
01:33:37,220 --> 01:33:39,540
Dad, I don't want
to get married now.

1343
01:33:40,020 --> 01:33:42,510
I want to finish my graduation
and then join the army, Dad.

1344
01:33:42,600 --> 01:33:44,290
You want to roam around
with your boyfriend...

1345
01:33:44,420 --> 01:33:46,430
...and join the army.
Wow!

1346
01:33:46,620 --> 01:33:48,830
You are my daughter. Don't try
to become equivalent to my son.

1347
01:33:59,800 --> 01:34:02,200
- Hasn’t Shikha Sharma quit yet?
- No, sir.

1348
01:34:05,620 --> 01:34:06,520
Good.

1349
01:34:42,140 --> 01:34:43,140
Oh, my God!

1350
01:34:44,630 --> 01:34:45,500
Hey.

1351
01:34:46,780 --> 01:34:47,970
It's a love bite, right?

1352
01:34:50,990 --> 01:34:52,710
What happened?
I am just asking.

1353
01:34:54,870 --> 01:34:55,800
You have a boyfriend, right?

1354
01:34:55,890 --> 01:34:57,690
Bilal, I don't want
to talk about this.

1355
01:35:00,630 --> 01:35:02,630
You met him last night,
didn't you?

1356
01:35:02,870 --> 01:35:04,880
Dude, I just said, I don't
want to talk about it.

1357
01:35:07,280 --> 01:35:08,150
All right.

1358
01:35:09,300 --> 01:35:10,890
We both are friends.
But it doesn't mean

1359
01:35:10,970 --> 01:35:13,360
that we share
everything about ourselves.

1360
01:35:15,580 --> 01:35:16,780
Why are you getting defensive?

1361
01:35:17,440 --> 01:35:18,560
There's no need for that.

1362
01:35:18,770 --> 01:35:19,700
In friendship...

1363
01:35:20,350 --> 01:35:22,410
...people usually share everything
with each other. Don't they?

1364
01:35:22,500 --> 01:35:23,420
I don't.

1365
01:35:25,060 --> 01:35:26,270
I need my space.

1366
01:35:28,950 --> 01:35:30,860
Bilal.
From now on, if you think

1367
01:35:30,940 --> 01:35:33,030
you shouldn't share
everything with me...

1368
01:35:33,110 --> 01:35:34,300
...then please don't.

1369
01:35:34,840 --> 01:35:37,370
Don't expect me to give you
my biodata, man.

1370
01:35:40,180 --> 01:35:41,610
Seems everyone is right.

1371
01:35:44,040 --> 01:35:45,920
- You are playing me.
- What?

1372
01:35:47,290 --> 01:35:48,740
What do you mean
by I'm playing you?

1373
01:35:49,460 --> 01:35:51,470
Because I didn't tell you
that I have a boyfriend?

1374
01:35:52,350 --> 01:35:54,340
He is my boyfriend.
That's my personal life.

1375
01:35:54,500 --> 01:35:56,020
How does it matter to you?

1376
01:35:56,800 --> 01:36:00,580
Did I come to you and ask you
to be my friend, my buddy...

1377
01:36:00,660 --> 01:36:01,710
...and to take care of me?

1378
01:36:02,120 --> 01:36:03,010
No.

1379
01:36:03,330 --> 01:36:05,740
If you are feeling bad
then please leave me alone.

1380
01:36:06,270 --> 01:36:08,390
Listen.
A word of advice, Shikha.

1381
01:36:09,280 --> 01:36:10,290
No one!

1382
01:36:10,620 --> 01:36:14,330
Absolutely no one
wins a battle on their own.

1383
01:36:14,950 --> 01:36:15,850
Got it?

1384
01:36:21,460 --> 01:36:24,680
One lakh, one thousand, two hundred
and eighty Indian army soldiers...

1385
01:36:25,110 --> 01:36:28,640
...are deployed in 16 peacekeeping
missions, worldwide.

1386
01:36:28,860 --> 01:36:30,880
In all these overseas operation...

1387
01:36:30,970 --> 01:36:33,150
...the special forces
play a special role.

1388
01:36:33,530 --> 01:36:37,070
The missions in which even
the toughest soldiers give up...

1389
01:36:37,370 --> 01:36:39,040
...we go to those missions
and operate.

1390
01:36:39,250 --> 01:36:42,180
That's why we put you all
such rigorous training.

1391
01:36:42,540 --> 01:36:43,420
[Whistle]

1392
01:36:46,930 --> 01:36:48,220
The one who survive this...

1393
01:36:48,310 --> 01:36:49,790
...can go through anything.

1394
01:36:50,520 --> 01:36:52,910
Come on, Capt. Rathore.
Get inside.

1395
01:37:03,170 --> 01:37:05,960
Are you scared, Capt. Manit?
Don't be scared.

1396
01:37:06,360 --> 01:37:07,560
[Bhatti] 'When the pain
becomes unbearable...'

1397
01:37:07,650 --> 01:37:08,920
[Bhatti] '...you stop feeling it.'

1398
01:37:09,010 --> 01:37:11,740
[Bhatti] 'Go ahead
and experience the pain.'

1399
01:37:11,830 --> 01:37:13,210
[Bhatti] 'Understand its value.'

1400
01:37:13,340 --> 01:37:15,670
[Bhatti] 'Your pain will
become your strength.'

1401
01:37:15,760 --> 01:37:18,090
[Bhatti] 'Your power to endure
will increase so much...'

1402
01:37:18,230 --> 01:37:22,170
[Bhatti] '...that you won't let
any kind of fear break you.'

1403
01:37:23,140 --> 01:37:24,510
Commando!

1404
01:37:40,470 --> 01:37:43,120
"I am used to winning."

1405
01:37:43,200 --> 01:37:45,800
"This is the end of enemies."

1406
01:37:45,880 --> 01:37:50,790
"- India is in my heart.
- India is in my heart."

1407
01:37:50,910 --> 01:37:56,190
"The motive of my life
is to protect my country."

1408
01:37:56,290 --> 01:38:01,090
"India is in my heart."

1409
01:38:01,370 --> 01:38:06,380
"I am not weak
nor less than anyone."

1410
01:38:06,590 --> 01:38:11,700
"I don't mind sacrificing my life."

1411
01:38:11,800 --> 01:38:16,990
"I am proud to say
that the tricolour is my life."

1412
01:38:17,070 --> 01:38:20,660
- "India is in my heart."
- Get the first aid. Hurry up.

1413
01:38:22,280 --> 01:38:27,290
"India is in my heart."

1414
01:38:27,380 --> 01:38:33,170
"India is in my heart."

1415
01:38:42,780 --> 01:38:49,960
"India is in my heart."

1416
01:38:53,580 --> 01:38:54,760
Commando!

1417
01:39:11,950 --> 01:39:13,400
As I always say...

1418
01:39:14,080 --> 01:39:15,920
...the weak have no place here.

1419
01:39:16,660 --> 01:39:17,660
The one who gets scared...

1420
01:39:18,630 --> 01:39:19,910
...will either go home...

1421
01:39:20,910 --> 01:39:22,020
...or lose his life.

1422
01:39:23,460 --> 01:39:25,460
We aren’t even halfway through
Dozakh yet, Captains.

1423
01:39:27,080 --> 01:39:29,070
Before we move ahead,
a 20 minute break.

1424
01:39:30,960 --> 01:39:33,490
- Let's take a nap.
- Yes, sir.

1425
01:39:41,620 --> 01:39:43,750
Don't take my words so seriously.

1426
01:39:45,030 --> 01:39:46,760
When I say break,
I mean your bones will break.

1427
01:39:48,030 --> 01:39:50,020
- Shall we move ahead!
- Yes, sir...

1428
01:39:50,580 --> 01:39:52,110
An uphill march for one hour...

1429
01:39:52,660 --> 01:39:54,670
...is waiting for you.

1430
01:39:55,790 --> 01:39:57,190
You have to bring the flag...

1431
01:39:57,320 --> 01:39:58,610
...from the checkpoint delta.

1432
01:39:59,280 --> 01:40:01,610
- Didn't you hear me?
- Yes, sir...

1433
01:40:01,850 --> 01:40:02,760
Come on.

1434
01:40:07,700 --> 01:40:08,680
What happened, Bilal?

1435
01:40:08,780 --> 01:40:10,200
Nothing.
Just a small cut.

1436
01:40:10,290 --> 01:40:13,800
Apply mud on it.
It will get healed.

1437
01:40:15,210 --> 01:40:19,000
- Bilal, you okay?
- I'm fine.

1438
01:40:22,770 --> 01:40:24,220
Is everything okay, Shikha?

1439
01:40:24,990 --> 01:40:26,970
[Siren]

1440
01:40:33,960 --> 01:40:34,830
Sir.

1441
01:40:37,150 --> 01:40:38,440
The results are here.

1442
01:40:42,010 --> 01:40:45,010
We have divided the probies
into two squads for the next task.

1443
01:40:46,200 --> 01:40:48,190
Capt. Rohan will lead Squad Alpha.

1444
01:40:48,430 --> 01:40:50,540
And Capt. Tank
will lead Squad Bravo.

1445
01:40:50,880 --> 01:40:51,870
Okay.
Thank you.

1446
01:40:55,070 --> 01:40:56,770
- Kripal.
- Sir.

1447
01:41:00,600 --> 01:41:03,320
No matter how well
one performs individually...

1448
01:41:03,520 --> 01:41:05,340
...in group or in the buddy
exercises...

1449
01:41:06,120 --> 01:41:08,650
...the biggest skill
for a commando...

1450
01:41:09,320 --> 01:41:10,240
...is leadership.

1451
01:41:14,630 --> 01:41:18,240
- You know what I mean.
- Sir.

1452
01:41:28,130 --> 01:41:32,930
[Moving car]

1453
01:41:33,970 --> 01:41:35,970
[Siren]

1454
01:41:41,320 --> 01:41:43,420
- Are you having fun?
- Yes, sir...

1455
01:41:43,500 --> 01:41:44,800
You'll enjoy it more now.

1456
01:41:46,060 --> 01:41:48,690
You are being divided
into two squads...

1457
01:41:50,480 --> 01:41:52,490
...for the second and the most
dangerous part of Dozakh.

1458
01:41:53,290 --> 01:41:58,100
Rohan, Manit, Bilal, Sharma,
Vishnu, Tej Bahadur.

1459
01:41:59,100 --> 01:42:00,480
You all are Squad Alpha.

1460
01:42:02,030 --> 01:42:03,810
Rest everyone is Squad Bravo.

1461
01:42:04,470 --> 01:42:05,450
Squad Bravo.

1462
01:42:05,670 --> 01:42:07,410
Your leader will be Capt. Tank.

1463
01:42:08,810 --> 01:42:10,540
And the one to lead
Squad Alpha is...

1464
01:42:11,450 --> 01:42:12,840
I'm sure it's Rathore.

1465
01:42:15,040 --> 01:42:16,030
Capt. Sharma.

1466
01:42:26,470 --> 01:42:27,670
Capt. Shikha Sharma.

1467
01:42:29,040 --> 01:42:30,650
You are not even able
to stand straight.

1468
01:42:31,780 --> 01:42:33,280
How are you going
to lead the squad?

1469
01:42:33,960 --> 01:42:34,960
I'll do it, sir.

1470
01:42:36,880 --> 01:42:39,380
Are you ready for the most
difficult challenge of Dozakh?

1471
01:42:39,730 --> 01:42:40,690
Yes, sir.

1472
01:42:40,780 --> 01:42:42,200
I can't hear you, Capt. Sharma.

1473
01:42:42,290 --> 01:42:43,430
Yes, sir!

1474
01:42:45,890 --> 01:42:46,770
Good.

1475
01:42:47,900 --> 01:42:48,910
Keep this in mind.

1476
01:43:06,520 --> 01:43:08,690
Tell her that she
is leaving against our will.

1477
01:43:08,800 --> 01:43:10,590
The doors of this house
are forever shut for her.

1478
01:43:17,270 --> 01:43:18,880
We loved her so much.
Where did we lack?

1479
01:43:18,990 --> 01:43:20,100
We got her educated.

1480
01:43:21,710 --> 01:43:23,020
And she isn't even
ready to listen to us.

1481
01:43:27,580 --> 01:43:29,810
I lost my son because of
this obsession with the army.

1482
01:43:31,380 --> 01:43:32,380
And now she is...

1483
01:44:00,390 --> 01:44:02,900
Don't feel bad
for what your dad said.

1484
01:44:03,450 --> 01:44:05,740
He is angry right now.
He'll be fine after a while.

1485
01:44:08,460 --> 01:44:11,040
You can go.
You must go.

1486
01:44:12,920 --> 01:44:15,160
I know one thing about you, Shikha.

1487
01:44:16,750 --> 01:44:18,740
You can achieve whatever you want.

1488
01:44:20,620 --> 01:44:22,910
And if someone stops you
from doing something...

1489
01:44:23,650 --> 01:44:25,760
...you will definitely do it.

1490
01:44:48,240 --> 01:44:50,050
[Mother] 'Just be careful.'

1491
01:44:50,190 --> 01:44:53,480
Actually, girls are changing
but not guys.

1492
01:44:54,160 --> 01:44:57,960
Guys don't like girls
who leave them behind.

1493
01:44:58,560 --> 01:45:00,260
Always keep this in mind.

1494
01:46:06,940 --> 01:46:08,080
March.

1495
01:46:14,260 --> 01:46:16,130
Come on... Fall in!
Hurry up.

1496
01:46:16,650 --> 01:46:17,770
Captains.

1497
01:46:18,160 --> 01:46:19,590
Till now, Mr. Naved and I...

1498
01:46:20,260 --> 01:46:24,380
...were here to hold your hand
just like a shadow.

1499
01:46:26,010 --> 01:46:27,250
Consider this a real mission...

1500
01:46:27,940 --> 01:46:29,130
...and not a task.

1501
01:46:29,980 --> 01:46:33,210
In these exercises,
live ammunition will be used.

1502
01:46:34,500 --> 01:46:35,630
Remember...

1503
01:46:35,860 --> 01:46:38,450
...ignorance can lead to disaster.

1504
01:46:40,410 --> 01:46:42,070
In the first stage,
you have to reach here.

1505
01:46:42,900 --> 01:46:44,120
Enemy's territory.

1506
01:46:45,310 --> 01:46:46,640
Point A for Squad Alpha.

1507
01:46:47,700 --> 01:46:49,060
Point X for Squad Bravo.

1508
01:46:50,300 --> 01:46:51,980
After reaching there,
if you succeed...

1509
01:46:52,300 --> 01:46:54,350
...you might find ration
to survive in the mission.

1510
01:46:55,270 --> 01:46:57,820
We'll be following you anyway.

1511
01:46:59,730 --> 01:47:02,510
You have only 10 minutes
to study the map.

1512
01:47:02,770 --> 01:47:03,820
Quick.

1513
01:47:10,310 --> 01:47:12,570
Okay, Vishnu. You and I will
be in charge of navigation.

1514
01:47:12,640 --> 01:47:14,040
Manit, you will be my 2IC.

1515
01:47:14,420 --> 01:47:17,030
Bilal, medical.
Tej, communication.

1516
01:47:17,220 --> 01:47:18,760
Capt. Rohan, weapons.

1517
01:47:21,520 --> 01:47:22,710
Any doubt, Capt. Rohan?

1518
01:47:28,920 --> 01:47:30,270
No, sir.

1519
01:47:33,360 --> 01:47:34,440
Did you all study the map?

1520
01:47:34,520 --> 01:47:36,270
- Yes, sir...
- Good.

1521
01:47:37,550 --> 01:47:38,550
Then give it back.

1522
01:47:44,890 --> 01:47:46,350
If you can’t do without a map..

1523
01:47:47,550 --> 01:47:48,840
...you are not worthy
to be in the special forces.

1524
01:47:49,880 --> 01:47:50,910
Yes, sir...

1525
01:47:52,490 --> 01:47:55,880
All the best, buddy. You have
to do the back seat driving.

1526
01:47:56,850 --> 01:47:59,480
You know how good women
are with directions, right?

1527
01:48:07,320 --> 01:48:08,420
Capt. Sharma.

1528
01:48:10,400 --> 01:48:11,490
Good luck.

1529
01:48:13,930 --> 01:48:15,110
Thank you.

1530
01:48:52,930 --> 01:48:53,870
Which way, Vishnu?

1531
01:48:53,950 --> 01:48:55,980
Left or right?

1532
01:48:59,640 --> 01:49:00,660
Let's go right.

1533
01:49:02,130 --> 01:49:03,220
You are wrong, Shikha.

1534
01:49:03,600 --> 01:49:05,680
We just crossed that hillock.

1535
01:49:05,970 --> 01:49:06,970
This is the right way.

1536
01:49:07,140 --> 01:49:08,290
Try to recall the map.

1537
01:49:08,490 --> 01:49:09,500
That hillock was in the north.

1538
01:49:09,700 --> 01:49:11,180
We need to go that way
and not this way.

1539
01:49:11,250 --> 01:49:12,330
I know what I am doing.

1540
01:49:12,570 --> 01:49:14,250
And I heard both of you talking.

1541
01:49:14,360 --> 01:49:16,350
Just because I'm a girl,
my navigation is wrong.

1542
01:49:16,430 --> 01:49:18,330
- When did I say that?
- You didn't but you thought so.

1543
01:49:18,470 --> 01:49:21,180
- Seriously, Shiks.
- Capt. Soren. It's Capt. Sharma.

1544
01:49:24,980 --> 01:49:26,990
Really?
So the authority card, huh?

1545
01:49:28,190 --> 01:49:30,840
Okay.
Cool.

1546
01:49:31,820 --> 01:49:32,830
Roger, ma'am.

1547
01:49:35,090 --> 01:49:36,700
We are going this way
and that's final.

1548
01:49:59,890 --> 01:50:00,930
Sir.

1549
01:50:01,540 --> 01:50:03,650
I marked this tree an hour ago.

1550
01:50:05,530 --> 01:50:07,680
We have come back
to the same point.

1551
01:50:11,440 --> 01:50:12,490
Great.

1552
01:50:12,790 --> 01:50:13,800
You know what?

1553
01:50:13,960 --> 01:50:16,160
Surje would've been really happy
if he were in our team.

1554
01:50:16,520 --> 01:50:18,820
We are prancing around a tree
like in a Hindi movie's song.

1555
01:50:20,240 --> 01:50:21,260
S**t!

1556
01:50:22,230 --> 01:50:23,460
Which way, Capt. Sharma?

1557
01:50:28,700 --> 01:50:29,950
I'm really sorry.

1558
01:50:32,200 --> 01:50:34,330
Let's go back to that hillock.

1559
01:50:35,530 --> 01:50:37,270
- We'll start navigating again...
- Negative.

1560
01:50:38,160 --> 01:50:41,180
Neither do we have time
nor do we need to go back.

1561
01:50:41,820 --> 01:50:43,080
Time and effort,
both will go waste.

1562
01:50:44,530 --> 01:50:45,910
Anyway, it's going to be dawn soon.

1563
01:50:46,790 --> 01:50:49,200
It'll be easier to navigate.
We should wait.

1564
01:50:50,140 --> 01:50:51,260
Makes sense.

1565
01:50:53,520 --> 01:50:55,390
I still think we should go back.

1566
01:51:04,310 --> 01:51:05,540
Okay, fine.

1567
01:51:06,680 --> 01:51:07,860
Halt till daybreak.

1568
01:51:08,510 --> 01:51:09,830
Capt. Rohan, weapons check.

1569
01:51:11,900 --> 01:51:14,080
- Vishnu.
- All in.

1570
01:51:17,090 --> 01:51:19,200
- Capt. Sharma.
- All in.

1571
01:51:19,590 --> 01:51:21,300
- Bilal.
- All in.

1572
01:51:27,610 --> 01:51:28,740
Sir.

1573
01:51:33,230 --> 01:51:34,460
One of my magazines is missing.

1574
01:51:34,540 --> 01:51:35,630
Manit.

1575
01:51:36,740 --> 01:51:38,300
- Manit.
- All in.

1576
01:51:38,590 --> 01:51:39,640
Tej.

1577
01:51:43,750 --> 01:51:44,950
All in, sir.

1578
01:51:47,530 --> 01:51:48,540
All in.

1579
01:51:49,350 --> 01:51:51,200
You can't make
everything official, Tej.

1580
01:51:52,110 --> 01:51:54,590
- It was there till we crossed
the last point, right? - Yes.

1581
01:51:54,730 --> 01:51:57,230
So, it has gone missing
somewhere in-between.

1582
01:51:58,610 --> 01:52:01,040
We are taking a halt.
Just go and search for it.

1583
01:52:17,170 --> 01:52:21,980
[Footsteps]

1584
01:52:45,440 --> 01:52:47,060
Vishnu and Manit, head west.

1585
01:52:47,150 --> 01:52:48,140
Rohan and Tej.

1586
01:52:48,220 --> 01:52:49,560
You will approach
the house from the east.

1587
01:52:49,630 --> 01:52:51,490
- Bilal will give cover. Copy?
- Copy.

1588
01:52:51,550 --> 01:52:52,710
Go.

1589
01:52:52,880 --> 01:52:56,300
[Footsteps]

1590
01:53:09,810 --> 01:53:10,970
[Whistle]

1591
01:53:16,730 --> 01:53:17,910
Alpha2 to Alpha1.

1592
01:53:18,030 --> 01:53:19,840
In position.
Twenty yards away.

1593
01:53:19,960 --> 01:53:21,420
The wall is broken.
Roof is missing.

1594
01:53:21,560 --> 01:53:23,660
There is complete silence.
No sign of activity. Over.

1595
01:53:23,780 --> 01:53:24,840
Alpha3, over.

1596
01:53:24,920 --> 01:53:25,920
Alpha3 in position.

1597
01:53:26,000 --> 01:53:28,240
There is a wall in front of me.
I can't see the house. Over.

1598
01:53:28,310 --> 01:53:30,680
Copy Alpha3, hold position.
Bilal, hold position.

1599
01:53:35,510 --> 01:53:38,190
Alpha2, you will go ahead.
We'll give you cover. Over.

1600
01:53:38,720 --> 01:53:42,620
Okay.
Moving in 3, 2, 1. Out.

1601
01:54:01,290 --> 01:54:06,100
[Footsteps]

1602
01:54:23,340 --> 01:54:25,670
Alpha1, all clear.
Over.

1603
01:54:26,910 --> 01:54:29,960
Copy. Squad Alpha.
Moving inside. Over.

1604
01:54:31,290 --> 01:54:32,770
Where is the food?

1605
01:54:34,550 --> 01:54:35,800
I swear, Vishnu.

1606
01:54:35,890 --> 01:54:38,940
Today I don't mind having bland,
boiled chicken served in the mess.

1607
01:54:39,840 --> 01:54:40,910
Yes, dude.

1608
01:54:41,350 --> 01:54:43,010
It's been 34 hours
since we had food.

1609
01:54:43,130 --> 01:54:44,700
Where is the food?

1610
01:54:47,420 --> 01:54:48,370
There it is.

1611
01:54:52,070 --> 01:54:55,530
Oh, s**t!
Don't move. It'll blast.

1612
01:54:56,720 --> 01:54:57,770
Take cover.

1613
01:55:00,200 --> 01:55:05,000
[Beeping sound]

1614
01:55:09,360 --> 01:55:10,430
Careful.

1615
01:55:10,850 --> 01:55:15,740
[Beeping sound]

1616
01:55:29,510 --> 01:55:30,820
What the f**k!

1617
01:55:31,370 --> 01:55:32,670
What the f**k!

1618
01:55:33,370 --> 01:55:38,250
[Beeping sound]

1619
01:55:38,430 --> 01:55:41,430
Alpha1, there is a bomb
here, not food.

1620
01:55:42,290 --> 01:55:44,010
It got activated as soon
as Vishnu stepped on it.

1621
01:55:44,630 --> 01:55:48,100
It's an IED.
I repeat, it's an IED.

1622
01:55:48,450 --> 01:55:50,020
It's a 155 mm shell.

1623
01:55:51,140 --> 01:55:52,530
It contains 6 kgs TNT...

1624
01:55:52,620 --> 01:55:53,980
...with blasting power
of 300 pounds.

1625
01:55:54,040 --> 01:55:55,330
[Vishnu] 'If I move even slightly,
everything around me...'

1626
01:55:55,420 --> 01:55:57,000
...in a 100 metre radius will
be destroyed.

1627
01:55:58,520 --> 01:56:00,910
Good to know because we are
just 30 metres away from you.

1628
01:56:01,450 --> 01:56:02,730
Manit, is there a timer?

1629
01:56:02,810 --> 01:56:04,800
I just said, it's a f*****g IED.

1630
01:56:04,900 --> 01:56:06,520
We just have 2 minutes 45 seconds.

1631
01:56:06,600 --> 01:56:07,940
Please order.

1632
01:56:09,280 --> 01:56:10,780
- Capt. Vishnu, hold position.
- Copy.

1633
01:56:10,840 --> 01:56:13,880
Capt. Manit, you have worked
with IED explosives before.

1634
01:56:13,960 --> 01:56:15,180
[Shikha] 'Correct?
Can you work this?'

1635
01:56:15,410 --> 01:56:17,360
I can do it.
But...

1636
01:56:18,590 --> 01:56:20,380
I would have to check
the blasting cap.

1637
01:56:20,720 --> 01:56:22,510
I'll get to know
once I find the source.

1638
01:56:23,440 --> 01:56:26,430
- Spring or pressure mechanism?
- Spring. But lots of wires.

1639
01:56:26,490 --> 01:56:29,860
Bhatti's favourite brand must
be United Colors of Benetton.

1640
01:56:29,940 --> 01:56:32,010
[Manit] 'B******d,
it's a rainbow of wires.'

1641
01:56:37,190 --> 01:56:38,400
Manit, hurry up.

1642
01:56:39,060 --> 01:56:41,650
F**k.
I am doing it, dude.

1643
01:56:41,730 --> 01:56:43,880
It's too hot. Can't f**k
around with it too much.

1644
01:56:44,590 --> 01:56:46,590
Manit, eliminate the
wires one by one...

1645
01:56:46,650 --> 01:56:47,810
...based on what they
are connected to.

1646
01:56:48,610 --> 01:56:51,570
This is not the video in, video
out lead of TV, Capt. Sharma.

1647
01:56:51,650 --> 01:56:53,920
You know you take stating
the obvious to another level.

1648
01:56:54,030 --> 01:56:56,490
Manit, please focus on your job.

1649
01:57:01,030 --> 01:57:02,350
Okay, it's not the green wire.

1650
01:57:06,740 --> 01:57:08,040
Black is out too.

1651
01:57:11,260 --> 01:57:12,880
75 seconds more, Manit.

1652
01:57:12,960 --> 01:57:14,720
I can see the damn numbers, dude!

1653
01:57:21,170 --> 01:57:22,070
Okay.

1654
01:57:22,170 --> 01:57:23,880
There are two wires.
Red and blue.

1655
01:57:24,200 --> 01:57:26,030
One of them is connected
to the blasting cap.

1656
01:57:26,180 --> 01:57:28,620
- If I cut the wrong one,
it'll blast. - F**k.

1657
01:57:30,010 --> 01:57:32,260
Okay, Manit.
Look carefully.

1658
01:57:32,570 --> 01:57:33,850
Where are the wires connected from?

1659
01:57:36,020 --> 01:57:37,540
Both are going into
the same box, dude.

1660
01:57:40,460 --> 01:57:41,580
- F**k.
- What?

1661
01:57:41,660 --> 01:57:42,850
- We are f****d.
- What...

1662
01:57:42,930 --> 01:57:44,260
Both wires have been stripped down.

1663
01:57:44,360 --> 01:57:45,380
Both have been tied...

1664
01:57:45,460 --> 01:57:47,040
...and connected
to an electric device...

1665
01:57:47,120 --> 01:57:48,320
...which is connected to the timer.

1666
01:57:50,200 --> 01:57:52,330
I think it's the red wire.
I'm going with the red.

1667
01:57:53,010 --> 01:57:55,190
- Wait.
- What, dude? We are losing time.

1668
01:57:55,270 --> 01:57:56,570
It's a trap.
Go with the blue.

1669
01:57:57,090 --> 01:57:58,280
Are you f*****g kidding me?

1670
01:57:58,360 --> 01:58:00,170
Bomb is in front of me.
The device is in my hand.

1671
01:58:00,260 --> 01:58:02,030
I feel I should cut the red wire.
I'm going with the red.

1672
01:58:02,130 --> 01:58:04,730
Manit, I have an instinct.
It's reverse psychology.

1673
01:58:04,810 --> 01:58:05,810
Go with the blue.

1674
01:58:06,060 --> 01:58:08,200
Instinct?
What about logic?

1675
01:58:08,580 --> 01:58:11,990
We lost many hours because
of your instinct, Capt. Sharma.

1676
01:58:12,090 --> 01:58:13,970
It's not the time for guess work.
I'm going with the red.

1677
01:58:14,350 --> 01:58:15,990
- Manit, blue. - Red.
- Blue.

1678
01:58:16,080 --> 01:58:17,840
- Red.
- Blue. It's an order.

1679
01:58:18,050 --> 01:58:20,250
- Manit, go with the red.
- Rohan, you stay out of this.

1680
01:58:21,060 --> 01:58:22,090
- Blue...
- Red...

1681
01:58:22,170 --> 01:58:23,100
Red!

1682
01:58:23,190 --> 01:58:25,440
[Beeping sound]

1683
01:58:29,530 --> 01:58:30,550
It stopped.

1684
01:58:30,900 --> 01:58:33,450
Vishnu, it stopped.
It stopped.

1685
01:58:33,850 --> 01:58:35,650
Vishnu, we are safe.

1686
01:58:36,480 --> 01:58:40,740
Hurray!
[Cheers]

1687
01:58:41,120 --> 01:58:42,970
[Manit] 'Die another day, b*tch!'

1688
01:58:46,330 --> 01:58:48,320
Well done, bro.

1689
01:58:50,130 --> 01:58:51,150
Close one.

1690
01:58:51,480 --> 01:58:53,440
- Seriously. Logic.
- Not instinct, but logic.

1691
01:58:54,860 --> 01:58:55,880
Well done, Manit.

1692
01:58:56,180 --> 01:58:58,700
But what you did
amounts to breach of orders.

1693
01:59:01,440 --> 01:59:03,050
Are you being serious?

1694
01:59:03,920 --> 01:59:07,080
Yeah. Manit didn't follow
the orders of his team leader.

1695
01:59:07,160 --> 01:59:09,210
Thank God he didn't
follow your orders.

1696
01:59:09,480 --> 01:59:11,290
Look what happened when
Vishnu followed your orders.

1697
01:59:11,400 --> 01:59:13,870
There is a reason there is a chain
of command in the army, okay?

1698
01:59:14,210 --> 01:59:16,200
And you out of all people
should know that.

1699
01:59:16,280 --> 01:59:17,170
Excuse me.

1700
01:59:17,240 --> 01:59:20,030
You need to be alive in order to
follow the orders, Capt. Sharma.

1701
01:59:20,520 --> 01:59:22,120
Are you upset with Manit
or with yourself...

1702
01:59:22,180 --> 01:59:23,750
...for two terrible judgements
in a row now?

1703
01:59:23,830 --> 01:59:26,620
- Stop getting personal, Bilal.
- I'm not getting personal.

1704
01:59:26,720 --> 01:59:28,590
Bilal, Shikha.
Time out, guys.

1705
01:59:33,680 --> 01:59:34,870
Shikha, come on.
We are a team.

1706
01:59:36,010 --> 01:59:36,960
We maybe a team.

1707
01:59:37,020 --> 01:59:39,230
But the last I checked
the army was not a democracy.

1708
01:59:40,060 --> 01:59:41,560
Unbelievable.

1709
01:59:41,930 --> 01:59:43,790
Just because you were
made the leader of this task

1710
01:59:44,050 --> 01:59:45,470
do you think you are God?

1711
01:59:48,320 --> 01:59:49,890
The entire jungle would
have burned to ashes...

1712
01:59:49,970 --> 01:59:51,350
...due to the amount of TNT
present in that bomb.

1713
01:59:51,490 --> 01:59:54,110
Okay. Guys, obviously
I'm glad, we are alive.

1714
01:59:54,190 --> 01:59:56,160
No, it's not that obvious.

1715
01:59:57,390 --> 01:59:58,740
Rules are rules.

1716
01:59:59,550 --> 02:00:00,670
That's the first thing
we are taught...

1717
02:00:00,750 --> 02:00:02,630
- ...when we come into the academy.
- What the f**k, dude!

1718
02:00:03,470 --> 02:00:06,010
S***a, I saved everyone's life.
This is the thanks I am getting.

1719
02:00:06,080 --> 02:00:07,330
Lower your voice!

1720
02:00:07,790 --> 02:00:08,850
I'm still your team leader.

1721
02:00:09,250 --> 02:00:10,730
Yeah. But maybe not on merit.

1722
02:00:10,960 --> 02:00:12,270
Excuse me.

1723
02:00:12,470 --> 02:00:15,990
I guess we all agree that our team
leader is wrong and we are right.

1724
02:00:16,530 --> 02:00:18,990
- And we know to set things right.
- Oh, really?

1725
02:00:20,030 --> 02:00:21,880
How, Capt. Rathore?

1726
02:00:23,020 --> 02:00:25,070
Do you really want
to know, Capt. Sharma?

1727
02:00:28,040 --> 02:00:32,610
[Moving car]

1728
02:00:36,140 --> 02:00:37,160
[Door close]

1729
02:00:39,750 --> 02:00:41,670
- Jai Hind, sir...
- Jai Hind.

1730
02:00:43,150 --> 02:00:44,210
At ease.

1731
02:00:46,500 --> 02:00:47,790
Any problem, Capt. Sharma?

1732
02:00:49,880 --> 02:00:52,250
- No, sir. - Are you sure?
- Yes, sir.

1733
02:00:54,030 --> 02:00:55,480
In that case,
well done, Squad Alpha.

1734
02:00:55,820 --> 02:00:57,780
You defused the bomb successfully.

1735
02:00:58,750 --> 02:01:02,030
Had it got detonated,
you wouldn't have lost your life

1736
02:01:02,280 --> 02:01:04,520
but could have been badly injured.

1737
02:01:05,430 --> 02:01:09,520
Anyway, Squad Bravo
completed the task an hour ago.

1738
02:01:11,340 --> 02:01:12,430
Let's move ahead.

1739
02:01:12,550 --> 02:01:14,480
The last and the most
dangerous task.

1740
02:01:15,040 --> 02:01:17,430
Ten kms ahead,
in the enemy's village...

1741
02:01:17,570 --> 02:01:18,880
...point B.

1742
02:01:19,660 --> 02:01:22,270
You'll have to retrieve a very
important packet from there.

1743
02:01:24,330 --> 02:01:26,050
And because you didn't
get anything to eat...

1744
02:01:27,140 --> 02:01:28,420
...you can eat these pills.

1745
02:01:30,150 --> 02:01:31,840
It will re-energise you.

1746
02:01:39,220 --> 02:01:40,330
Chew it.

1747
02:01:48,220 --> 02:01:51,150
These are not vitamin pills.
These are sleeping pills.

1748
02:01:52,470 --> 02:01:54,570
These pills will prepare
you for the day...

1749
02:01:54,770 --> 02:01:56,620
...when you would complete
your operation without sleeping...

1750
02:01:56,680 --> 02:01:58,630
...not for hours but for days.

1751
02:01:59,610 --> 02:02:00,850
Despite being deprived of sleep...

1752
02:02:01,010 --> 02:02:03,450
...you'll have to be alert
and take the right decision.

1753
02:02:04,040 --> 02:02:05,060
The one who sleeps today...

1754
02:02:05,560 --> 02:02:08,890
...might go to sleep forever,
during a real operation.

1755
02:02:11,360 --> 02:02:15,300
[Birds chirping]

1756
02:02:20,960 --> 02:02:24,030
[Shikha] 'If he can do it, so can I.'

1757
02:02:24,960 --> 02:02:28,500
[Shikha] 'If they could do it,
even we'll be able to.'

1758
02:02:29,750 --> 02:02:32,970
[Shikha] 'If he can do it, so can I.'

1759
02:02:34,410 --> 02:02:35,990
[Shikha] 'If they could..'

1760
02:02:47,690 --> 02:02:49,510
I can't do this anymore.

1761
02:02:50,260 --> 02:02:51,500
We can do it.

1762
02:02:51,580 --> 02:02:53,810
She is so stubborn.

1763
02:02:55,240 --> 02:02:57,150
I say, stop this game, dude.

1764
02:02:57,990 --> 02:03:02,180
We can do it.
I can do it.

1765
02:03:05,450 --> 02:03:08,410
[Gun shots]

1766
02:03:08,650 --> 02:03:10,070
Everybody, take cover.

1767
02:03:11,200 --> 02:03:13,300
Retaliate.
It's an ambush!

1768
02:03:13,790 --> 02:03:15,060
Everybody, take cover!

1769
02:03:18,300 --> 02:03:20,000
Tej, Vishnu.
Right side.

1770
