1908
02:16:22,750 --> 02:16:24,090
Okay.
Put him on.

1909
02:16:25,760 --> 02:16:29,600
Yes, Mr. Mathur.
She is doing fine.

1910
02:16:31,370 --> 02:16:32,540
It's in three weeks.

1911
02:16:34,460 --> 02:16:37,200
All right.
It shall be arranged.

1912
02:16:39,380 --> 02:16:40,610
The defence minister
herself wants to attend

1913
02:16:40,920 --> 02:16:43,210
the passing out parade of the SFTC.

1914
02:16:45,130 --> 02:16:46,650
POP is in three weeks’ time.

1915
02:16:46,910 --> 02:16:48,150
Bloody hell.

1916
02:16:49,100 --> 02:16:51,170
Looks like, we are sitting
on a ticking time bomb.

1917
02:17:02,140 --> 02:17:03,570
- Good morning, sir.
- Relax.

1918
02:17:04,090 --> 02:17:05,230
How are you feeling now?

1919
02:17:05,320 --> 02:17:08,320
Very well, sir. Thank you.
Thank you for asking, sir.

1920
02:17:11,430 --> 02:17:13,090
I still didn't receive
the RMO's report.

1921
02:17:13,180 --> 02:17:14,950
But looking at you...

1922
02:17:15,030 --> 02:17:18,380
...it seems you will
take time to recover.

1923
02:17:21,390 --> 02:17:22,870
Capt. Sharma, you know...

1924
02:17:22,960 --> 02:17:26,480
...that Capt. Siddiqui had
to leave after Dozakh.

1925
02:17:26,760 --> 02:17:28,790
You also know
Capt. Surje's condition.

1926
02:17:30,890 --> 02:17:33,550
I am trying to say that so
far you've done everything...

1927
02:17:34,070 --> 02:17:36,580
...with passion, preparation
and commitment.

1928
02:17:38,050 --> 02:17:39,870
But after recovering...

1929
02:17:40,090 --> 02:17:41,990
