The First Test Case!

2021
02:23:01,580 --> 02:23:02,820
You can't be serious, sir.

2022
02:23:02,910 --> 02:23:04,850
I genuinely hope
that this isn't true.

2023
02:23:06,650 --> 02:23:09,730
If it is then we need to
bring the culprit to book.

2024
02:23:11,080 --> 02:23:12,500
He should be punished
so severely...

2025
02:23:12,590 --> 02:23:16,110
...that no one should even think
of doing something like this.

2026
02:23:20,280 --> 02:23:21,790
Language is quite clinical.

2027
02:23:22,530 --> 02:23:25,360
He has written adm for
administration and not admin.

2028
02:23:25,880 --> 02:23:28,450
cdr for commander
and coa for company.

2029
02:23:28,970 --> 02:23:30,350
Army abbreviations.

2030
02:23:31,490 --> 02:23:33,890
And look at this, sir.
Time stamp.

2031
02:23:34,420 --> 02:23:36,600
Only soldiers use
such kind of time stamp.

2032
02:23:37,350 --> 02:23:39,830
It means that certainly
this mail has been sent...

2033
02:23:41,090 --> 02:23:42,720
...by someone from the SFTC.

2034
02:23:45,370 --> 02:23:46,470
Anything else?

2035
02:23:47,360 --> 02:23:48,890
I read Capt. Shikha's file...

2036
02:23:48,980 --> 02:23:51,170
...when she was chosen
for the Test Case.

2037
02:23:52,030 --> 02:23:54,710
She is a shooting champion
but quite emotional as well.

2038
02:23:55,690 --> 02:23:57,630
And being emotional
in the special forces...

2039
02:23:58,090 --> 02:23:59,360
...is like inviting danger.

2040
02:24:02,630 --> 02:24:04,370
You have three weeks.

2041
02:24:05,090 --> 02:24:06,530
You need to resolve this case...

2042
02:24:06,690 --> 02:24:08,040
...before the course ends.

2043
02:24:09,370 --> 02:24:11,010
Roger, sir.
Wilco.

2044
02:24:11,270 --> 02:24:13,960
Will comply.
And you.

2045
02:24:16,400 --> 02:24:18,010
Got my poker face on, sir.

2046
02:25:11,730 --> 02:25:13,480
Will you finish the packing
today itself, Mom?

2047
02:25:14,100 --> 02:25:15,510
My train is scheduled
to leave tomorrow evening

2048
02:25:16,000 --> 02:25:17,340
You are going to join
the special forces.

2049
02:25:17,530 --> 02:25:18,900
Everything should be perfect.

2050
02:25:19,790 --> 02:25:22,550
You seem to know the
special forces very well.

2051
02:25:23,180 --> 02:25:24,080
Why?

2052
02:25:24,630 --> 02:25:27,560
Didn't I spend so many
years with your dad?

2053
02:25:28,530 --> 02:25:30,720
Even the toughest
people give up there.

2054
02:25:31,260 --> 02:25:32,750
It's a very difficult course, dear.

2055
02:25:33,080 --> 02:25:34,330
I see.

2056
02:25:34,620 --> 02:25:37,820
It seems as if Sakshi Malik
is going for a wrestling match.

2057
02:25:38,270 --> 02:25:42,030
You're more excited than me to
see me in the SF's uniform. Right?

2058
02:25:43,620 --> 02:25:46,760
The uniform and the status
are two different things.

2059
02:25:47,760 --> 02:25:49,040
You got the uniform.

2060
02:25:49,300 --> 02:25:50,640
Now, you need to earn the status.

2061
02:25:52,020 --> 02:25:53,450
Keep one thing in mind, dear.

2062
02:25:54,100 --> 02:25:55,390
This is an opportunity...

2063
02:25:55,850 --> 02:25:59,870
...which your grandma
and your mom didn't get.

2064
02:26:01,020 --> 02:26:02,380
Only you got it.

2065
02:26:04,140 --> 02:26:05,550
No matter what...

2066
02:26:06,660 --> 02:26:08,300
...never give up, dear.

2067
02:26:12,200 --> 02:26:13,840
You are the most special girl...

2068
02:26:14,360 --> 02:26:17,010
...that is why you are going
to join the special force.

2069
02:26:19,830 --> 02:26:22,180
So cute, my Mom.

2070
02:26:22,270 --> 02:26:25,590
What do you keep blabbering
all day long in English?

2071
02:26:25,750 --> 02:26:27,500
I don't understand a single word.

2072
02:26:28,310 --> 02:26:30,700
Listen to me carefully, Mom.

2073
02:26:31,860 --> 02:26:35,420
Neither I nor you
or grandma will lose.

2074
02:26:36,280 --> 02:26:37,580
Do you know why?

2075
02:26:38,260 --> 02:26:40,740
Because my mom
didn't teach me to lose.

2076
02:26:43,090 --> 02:26:44,530
If you ever lose...

2077
02:26:45,540 --> 02:26:47,530
...I'll break your legs.

2078
02:26:50,550 --> 02:26:51,600
Sure.

2079
02:27:32,730 --> 02:27:33,710
Ma'am.

2080
02:27:35,300 --> 02:27:37,160
Shikha.
Shikha.

2081
02:27:38,280 --> 02:27:39,670
Shikha, what are you doing?

2082
02:27:40,840 --> 02:27:42,430
Shikha, you need some more time.

2083
02:27:42,520 --> 02:27:45,800
I don't have the time.
I need to complete the course.

2084
02:27:46,260 --> 02:27:47,560
And what about your injuries?

2085
02:27:48,130 --> 02:27:51,180
What'd you do when Colonel Sathe
will read your reports?

2086
02:27:52,890 --> 02:27:54,720
The injuries are mine
so the story will also be mine.

2087
02:27:55,600 --> 02:27:57,620
Everyone will have
to believe what I say.

2088
02:27:59,130 --> 02:28:01,310
- Are you sure about this?
- Affirmative.

2089
02:28:02,600 --> 02:28:05,440
Anyway the entire Squad Alpha
said that nothing happened.

2090
02:28:07,460 --> 02:28:08,730
So, nothing happened.

2091
02:28:12,040 --> 02:28:16,120
"I shall help you soar high."

2092
02:28:17,240 --> 02:28:21,690
"I shall fight this battle.
Just resolve to win."

2093
02:28:21,970 --> 02:28:24,370
"Just resolve to win."

2094
02:28:31,380 --> 02:28:32,750
[Surje] 'Who is this hero?'

2095
02:28:32,830 --> 02:28:34,090
He came into the picture...

2096
02:28:34,170 --> 02:28:35,510
...like Sunny Deol in Damini.

2097
02:28:36,340 --> 02:28:37,900
[Rohan] 'Colonel Imtiyaz Hussain.'

2098
02:28:38,010 --> 02:28:41,210
General Raman's son-in-law.
Sorry. Ex-son-in-law.

2099
02:28:41,810 --> 02:28:43,650
Few people are very evolved.

2100
02:28:43,860 --> 02:28:46,380
Husband and wife are good
friends even after divorce.

2101
02:28:46,730 --> 02:28:48,570
They celebrate all
the festivals together.

2102
02:28:49,120 --> 02:28:50,870
Then they go back
to their respective homes.

2103
02:28:53,340 --> 02:28:55,200
I wish every marriage
was like this.

2104
02:28:55,600 --> 02:28:59,190
Wives would've visited on festivals
and then gone back to their houses.

2105
02:28:59,810 --> 02:29:00,950
The point is, B*******d...

2106
02:29:01,030 --> 02:29:02,500
...which festival has he
come to celebrate here?

2107
02:29:02,580 --> 02:29:05,860
A few festivals are celebrated
while a few are observed, Surje.

2108
02:29:06,080 --> 02:29:07,880
[Avinash] 'I think he fits
into the second category.'

2109
02:29:07,950 --> 02:29:10,420
- Maybe he is our new instructor.
- I don't think so.

2110
02:29:10,500 --> 02:29:11,780
[Shikha] 'Good morning, gentlemen.'

2111
02:29:12,800 --> 02:29:13,820
What did I miss?

2112
02:29:13,910 --> 02:29:15,390
[Surje] 'You here!'

2113
02:29:15,840 --> 02:29:17,100
Aren't you happy to see me here?

2114
02:29:17,160 --> 02:29:19,890
What are you saying, ma'am?
We are obviously happy to see you.

2115
02:29:20,470 --> 02:29:22,030
Good to see you
back on your feet.

2116
02:29:22,200 --> 02:29:25,040
Thanks, Surje. I missed
your jokes, dude, actually.

2117
02:29:25,560 --> 02:29:28,080
What will we do during the war
if we get scared in Dozakh?

2118
02:29:28,210 --> 02:29:29,350
[Surje] You are right.

2119
02:29:31,580 --> 02:29:34,270
- Good to see you, Capt. Sharma.
- Tank.

2120
02:29:34,640 --> 02:29:37,110
I am sorry that Bilal had to leave.

2121
02:29:39,510 --> 02:29:42,190
Even I regret that I couldn't
meet him before he left.

2122
02:29:58,840 --> 02:30:01,570
Good morning, officers.
Lieutenant Colonel Imtiyaz Hussain.

2123
02:30:01,650 --> 02:30:02,450
Good morning, sir...

2124
02:30:02,530 --> 02:30:05,460
Let's cut to the chase.
I'm not your new instructor.

2125
02:30:05,540 --> 02:30:07,660
In fact I'm here
for a special purpose.

2126
02:30:08,720 --> 02:30:11,580
Squad Bravo, you may leave.

2127
02:30:34,480 --> 02:30:35,640
In poker they say...

2128
02:30:35,720 --> 02:30:37,960
...if you can't read
your opponent's cards...

2129
02:30:38,480 --> 02:30:40,230
...you better play
only with a good hand.

2130
02:30:41,210 --> 02:30:43,260
What happened in Camp
Dozakh, Squad Alpha...

2131
02:30:43,380 --> 02:30:46,580
...that Capt. Siddiqui
had to go home...

2132
02:30:47,760 --> 02:30:49,830
...and Capt. Sharma,
to the hospital?

2133
02:30:52,990 --> 02:30:54,290
Somebody?

2134
02:30:55,100 --> 02:30:56,380
[Imtiyaz] 'Anybody?'

2135
02:30:58,020 --> 02:30:59,380
Nobody.

2136
02:31:01,630 --> 02:31:03,810
I've read your debrief reports.

2137
02:31:04,210 --> 02:31:06,280
And according to
all your reports...

2138
02:31:06,360 --> 02:31:07,950
...nothing happened over there.

2139
02:31:10,070 --> 02:31:14,630
But we got an anonymous mail.
According to which...

2140
02:31:14,720 --> 02:31:17,250
...not something but many
things happened there.

2141
02:31:20,250 --> 02:31:24,340
So, whom do we believe?
An anonymous mail...

2142
02:31:24,410 --> 02:31:27,410
...or the officers
of the Indian army?

2143
02:31:29,250 --> 02:31:31,040
I think officers
of the Indian army.

2144
02:31:31,290 --> 02:31:34,080
So, I want to give you all
one more chance...

2145
02:31:35,940 --> 02:31:41,120
...to recount what
exactly happened.

2146
02:31:46,960 --> 02:31:49,470
This happens many times...

2147
02:31:49,550 --> 02:31:51,560
...a few details becomes
sketchy during actions.

2148
02:31:51,720 --> 02:31:56,850
So this time, write after recalling
the things properly. Please.

2149
02:32:01,340 --> 02:32:04,880
Last time you couldn't write
your debrief report, Capt. Sharma.

2150
02:32:05,290 --> 02:32:08,110
Looking forward to
reading your report. - Sir.

2151
02:32:47,570 --> 02:32:49,580
[Surje] 'What have you
guys done as such...'

2152
02:32:49,650 --> 02:32:52,200
...that he had to come
here to solve the issue?

2153
02:32:52,480 --> 02:32:54,220
Surje, you can't joke always.

2154
02:32:54,390 --> 02:32:56,430
Bravo's number might be next.

2155
02:32:56,550 --> 02:32:58,750
Do you know the SF has
become very strict nowadays?

2156
02:32:58,960 --> 02:33:00,960
For every failure, a new
committee initiates an enquiry.

2157
02:33:01,170 --> 02:33:03,910
Everything is monitored
very closely, Surje.

2158
02:33:03,990 --> 02:33:06,070
A committee will be set up
if there is a failure.

2159
02:33:06,230 --> 02:33:09,130
Check the leader board. For now,
all the Bravos are in the top.

2160
02:33:28,380 --> 02:33:29,710
S**t.

2161
02:33:49,940 --> 02:33:51,610
What, Surje?
Again?

2162
02:33:55,530 --> 02:33:58,220
These are combat injuries.
They'll heal.

2163
02:34:01,980 --> 02:34:06,520
Sorry, Capt. Sharma.
Please take care of yourself.

2164
02:34:18,110 --> 02:34:20,110
Thank you for all
the support, guys.

2165
02:34:54,780 --> 02:34:56,550
"Thanks for the support."

2166
02:34:57,760 --> 02:35:00,710
Was she thanking one of us
for sending that e-mail?

2167
02:35:02,010 --> 02:35:04,120
But why would any one
of us send that mail?

2168
02:35:04,310 --> 02:35:07,020
Yes. But when we have written
everything in the debrief...

2169
02:35:08,080 --> 02:35:09,090
...what was in that e-mail?

2170
02:35:09,170 --> 02:35:12,400
We know what we wrote
in the debriefing.

2171
02:35:12,590 --> 02:35:14,230
We don't know what she has written.

2172
02:35:14,530 --> 02:35:18,210
But why would she send a mail if
she was writing it in the report?

2173
02:35:18,570 --> 02:35:21,220
I think someone else did this.
- Like who?

2174
02:35:22,630 --> 02:35:26,630
A friend or a well-wisher.

2175
02:35:29,650 --> 02:35:32,160
Well, Bilal was her
good friend amongst us.

2176
02:35:32,700 --> 02:35:37,120
No, sir. Capt. Bilal can't do this.
He wrote what he was told.

2177
02:35:37,220 --> 02:35:41,360
Nobody told him.
He wrote what happened.

2178
02:35:43,700 --> 02:35:47,920
I hope... I hope we all
wrote what happened.

2179
02:36:12,690 --> 02:36:14,200
B******t, Imtiyaz!

2180
02:36:14,300 --> 02:36:15,940
I think you didn't read
the debriefs properly.

2181
02:36:16,020 --> 02:36:17,860
I read all the reports, sir.

2182
02:36:18,230 --> 02:36:20,580
And they are all worded
exactly the same.

2183
02:36:20,660 --> 02:36:22,040
Not a single word changed.

2184
02:36:22,130 --> 02:36:23,560
It means what Shikha has written...

2185
02:36:23,640 --> 02:36:25,840
...is what the entire Squad Alpha
wrote. Am I right?

2186
02:36:25,920 --> 02:36:28,710
Right, sir.
- They are the SFTC commandos.

2187
02:36:29,070 --> 02:36:31,540
They are trained to remember
things even while asleep.

2188
02:36:31,780 --> 02:36:34,740
If everyone has written the
same thing then this is the truth.

2189
02:36:38,180 --> 02:36:42,790
Even if I agree that everyone is
lying then what about Shikha?

2190
02:36:42,970 --> 02:36:46,020
Why is she lying?
- We need to find out that, sir.

2191
02:36:46,700 --> 02:36:49,330
Maybe she is being
pressurised to say this.

2192
02:36:49,430 --> 02:36:51,800
Or maybe it's all a cover-up.

2193
02:36:57,050 --> 02:37:02,220
Lt. Colonel Hussain,
are you pointing a finger at me?

2194
02:37:05,760 --> 02:37:09,990
No, sir. All I'm saying is that
everyone is a suspect for me...

2195
02:37:10,070 --> 02:37:13,480
...and every reason is valid,
until the truth comes out.

2196
02:37:13,560 --> 02:37:17,080
This...
This is the truth, Imtiyaz.

2197
02:37:19,580 --> 02:37:21,140
If something like this
had happened...

2198
02:37:21,320 --> 02:37:24,640
...then I would have been
the first person to find it out.

2199
02:37:27,110 --> 02:37:29,080
Sir, with all due respect...

2200
02:37:30,220 --> 02:37:32,120
...either you co-operate
with me now...

2201
02:37:32,750 --> 02:37:34,930
...or wait for an official
investigation.

2202
02:37:40,180 --> 02:37:41,430
I see.

2203
02:37:53,810 --> 02:37:55,530
Lt. Colonel Hussain.

2204
02:37:57,060 --> 02:37:59,930
You and me, us...

2205
02:38:00,760 --> 02:38:04,580
...sitting in my office
and talking about this...

2206
02:38:05,640 --> 02:38:08,970
...means me
co-operating with you.

2207
02:38:14,470 --> 02:38:17,550
Do you think it'll be easy
to find out the truth?

2208
02:38:19,060 --> 02:38:20,770
They are the SFTC commandos.

2209
02:38:21,750 --> 02:38:24,940
If they have decided
to conceal the truth...

2210
02:38:27,840 --> 02:38:30,040
...then they'll take it
to their graves.

2211
02:38:33,040 --> 02:38:37,550
Cardinal rule of poker, sir.
If all the players are bluffing...

2212
02:38:37,610 --> 02:38:39,540
...we should raise the stakes.

2213
02:38:39,870 --> 02:38:43,370
So that the weakest player
folds first.

2214
02:38:46,360 --> 02:38:48,190
[Locker opening]

2215
02:38:52,230 --> 02:38:53,800
[Locker closing]

2216
02:38:57,050 --> 02:38:59,900
"So, Bilal had multiple
fractures in the leg."

2217
02:38:59,980 --> 02:39:01,750
"Injury in his head
and concussion."

2218
02:39:01,830 --> 02:39:03,890
"Rohan had bruises
from falling on the rocks."

2219
02:39:04,010 --> 02:39:06,560
"And Vishnu's right side
was completely stiff."

2220
02:39:07,420 --> 02:39:08,550
And Shikha?

2221
02:39:10,020 --> 02:39:13,020
Which side of Shikha's head
had wounds?

2222
02:39:13,780 --> 02:39:17,140
- Sir. It's all in the report, sir.
- Oh.

2223
02:39:19,490 --> 02:39:22,120
Yeah.
On the right.

2224
02:39:24,070 --> 02:39:26,290
- What is for lunch?
- What?

2225
02:39:26,370 --> 02:39:28,210
Smells like paratha.

2226
02:39:28,550 --> 02:39:29,920
Aloo paratha.

2227
02:39:33,730 --> 02:39:35,510
Sir, will you have it?

2228
02:39:35,590 --> 02:39:38,440
Now that you are insisting,
I'll have it. Fine.

2229
02:39:43,250 --> 02:39:48,410
Thank you. Clarified butter.

2230
02:39:49,210 --> 02:39:53,040
Are the doctors allowed to
have clarified butter? It's good.

2231
02:39:55,370 --> 02:39:58,130
What do you think after looking
at Capt. Shikha's injuries?

2232
02:39:58,700 --> 02:40:01,840
Are these regular combat injuries?

2233
02:40:02,370 --> 02:40:06,660
Yes, sir. According to the patient
these are combat injuries.

2234
02:40:06,740 --> 02:40:08,560
It could be sexual assault as well.

2235
02:40:08,950 --> 02:40:10,940
Well... I just told you, sir...

2236
02:40:11,020 --> 02:40:13,370
...that according to the patient,
they are combat injuries.

2237
02:40:13,450 --> 02:40:15,100
Are you a lawyer or a doctor?

2238
02:40:16,570 --> 02:40:21,040
Capt. Aparna, you very well know
how to catch someone lying.

2239
02:40:24,770 --> 02:40:27,590
The heart beats faster.

2240
02:40:28,700 --> 02:40:30,480
Are you sure that Capt. Shikha
didn't fall unconscious...

2241
02:40:30,560 --> 02:40:32,290
...because of some other reason?

2242
02:40:32,630 --> 02:40:34,800
- Like what, sir?
- It could be anything.

2243
02:40:35,320 --> 02:40:36,880
She could be pregnant.

2244
02:40:37,690 --> 02:40:41,470
Sorry, sir. But why
would she be pregnant?

2245
02:40:41,550 --> 02:40:43,360
There are lots of
good looking men around.

2246
02:40:43,440 --> 02:40:46,930
They all stay in the same dorm.
Surely she is not a virgin.

2247
02:40:47,730 --> 02:40:50,490
Sir, I can't believe you
just asked me this question.

2248
02:40:52,440 --> 02:40:56,320
Relax.
These are just routine questions.

2249
02:40:56,600 --> 02:40:59,830
Sir, would you ask these routine
questions if she were a man?

2250
02:40:59,910 --> 02:41:01,660
Would you have been able
to answer this question...

2251
02:41:01,870 --> 02:41:02,810
...if she were a man?

2252
02:41:05,920 --> 02:41:07,870
Anyway, thank you.

2253
02:41:12,170 --> 02:41:14,660
Shikha's best quality
is that she is loyal.

2254
02:41:15,690 --> 02:41:19,300
She is loyal to her country.
She is loyal to her team.

2255
02:41:19,900 --> 02:41:21,860
And she is loyal to her boyfriend.

2256
02:41:22,190 --> 02:41:24,940
Loyalty is a strange quality,
Capt. Aparna.

2257
02:41:25,790 --> 02:41:29,720
You know, sometimes when
you are loyal to a person...

2258
02:41:30,140 --> 02:41:32,520
...you end up being disloyal
to the institution.

2259
02:41:33,090 --> 02:41:35,010
You understand what I am saying?

2260
02:41:36,670 --> 02:41:38,080
Yes, sir.

2261
02:41:38,970 --> 02:41:41,620
- Sir, I have patients waiting.
- Last question.

2262
02:41:42,850 --> 02:41:45,860
There were no nail marks on any
other member of Squad Alpha...

2263
02:41:45,960 --> 02:41:48,900
...other than Capt. Shikha.
Am I right?

2264
02:41:50,530 --> 02:41:51,800
Yes, sir.

2265
02:41:54,810 --> 02:41:58,830
Check your pulse rate,
Capt. Aparna. It's quite fast.

2266
02:42:07,520 --> 02:42:11,060
Capt. Shikha Sharma has a
boyfriend. Study boyfriend.

2267
02:42:11,360 --> 02:42:14,850
And RMO Capt. Aparna is trying
to hide something for sure.

2268
02:42:24,150 --> 02:42:27,080
Listen. Show me the register.
- Yes.

2269
02:42:27,510 --> 02:42:29,500
- Who are you, sir?
- Police Special Branch.

2270
02:42:31,410 --> 02:42:32,910
What happened, sir?

2271
02:42:38,580 --> 02:42:41,430
4th July,
Saturday night at 10:01...

2272
02:42:41,510 --> 02:42:43,290
...this mail was sent
from this IP address.

2273
02:42:43,380 --> 02:42:45,410
But there is no entry
for that time in this register.

2274
02:42:45,540 --> 02:42:49,430
It's a crime to use cyber cafe
without an ID. You know it, right?

2275
02:42:49,730 --> 02:42:51,720
Sir, it's the closing time.

2276
02:42:51,870 --> 02:42:55,210
- Sometimes it happens.
- "Sometimes."

2277
02:42:55,930 --> 02:42:58,700
I am sure, that time must
have been chosen on purpose.

2278
02:42:59,750 --> 02:43:02,190
Try to recall.
It happened last week.

2279
02:43:02,580 --> 02:43:04,580
It's a small town. I'm sure
many people don't come here.

2280
02:43:04,680 --> 02:43:06,370
Try to recollect who it was.

2281
02:43:09,340 --> 02:43:13,580
A tall guy, fair, muscular.
With the crutches...

2282
02:43:13,660 --> 02:43:15,680
I mean, he must have been
using crutches to walk.

2283
02:43:18,250 --> 02:43:21,630
Yes, sir.
A tall man had come here.

2284
02:43:21,730 --> 02:43:24,830
- Tall?
- Yes, sir. Tall.

2285
02:43:25,180 --> 02:43:28,920
He was wearing a jacket.

2286
02:43:29,500 --> 02:43:33,920
There was a muffler
around his neck.

2287
02:43:33,980 --> 02:43:36,020
- Just...
- Muffler?

2288
02:43:36,090 --> 02:43:38,490
Yes, sir. It was of this colour.
Red colour.

2289
02:43:46,770 --> 02:43:47,770
This...

2290
02:43:48,480 --> 02:43:51,300
Sir, it's not working
since two months.

2291
02:43:54,380 --> 02:43:55,790
Here is what you can do.

2292
02:43:55,880 --> 02:43:59,300
- Close this cyber cafe as well.
- What, sir?

2293
02:44:00,320 --> 02:44:02,120
[Car moving]

2294
02:44:02,200 --> 02:44:04,550
[Imtiyaz] 'It is said
that in war as in poker...'

2295
02:44:04,620 --> 02:44:06,340
[Imtiyaz] '...if you
want to win...'

2296
02:44:06,420 --> 02:44:09,160
...you should know the strengths
and weaknesses of each other.

2297
02:44:09,940 --> 02:44:11,950
And you all have...

2298
02:44:13,340 --> 02:44:14,820
...overcome Dozakh together.

2299
02:44:15,680 --> 02:44:20,580
But do you really know each
other? So, your task today is...

2300
02:44:20,930 --> 02:44:24,150
...to write down the strengths and
weaknesses of your course mates...

2301
02:44:24,230 --> 02:44:27,950
...in these forms. Through this,
we will collate the data...

2302
02:44:28,110 --> 02:44:31,220
...and make your
psychological profiles.

2303
02:44:31,300 --> 02:44:34,740
And don't worry.
Your views will be confidential.

2304
02:44:35,540 --> 02:44:38,660
So please, be brutal.

2305
02:44:41,040 --> 02:44:43,930
[Imtiyaz] 'Red ones for strength.
Blue for weaknesses.'

2306
02:44:44,210 --> 02:44:46,510
And your time starts now.

2307
02:45:08,060 --> 02:45:09,840
[Surje] 'B*******d.'

2308
02:45:12,510 --> 02:45:14,560
This is betrayal, boss.

2309
02:45:16,440 --> 02:45:18,820
That s***a said that the reports
would be confidential.

2310
02:45:19,030 --> 02:45:20,640
And he leaked it so easily.

2311
02:45:23,550 --> 02:45:26,140
What is this, Vishnu?
You think I am horny.

2312
02:45:26,710 --> 02:45:29,450
Just because I crack jokes,
you wrote this in my report!

2313
02:45:29,720 --> 02:45:31,730
Joking around is fine
among ourselves, Vishnu.

2314
02:45:32,340 --> 02:45:34,190
You know this will f**k my ACR.

2315
02:45:34,250 --> 02:45:36,550
Surje, sorry.
I thought it's confidential...

2316
02:45:36,630 --> 02:45:38,290
Whatever I'm, I'm upfront.

2317
02:45:38,380 --> 02:45:40,870
I am not like you guys.
God knows what you guys did...

2318
02:45:41,060 --> 02:45:43,530
...that the James Bond had to
come for the combing operation.

2319
02:45:45,090 --> 02:45:46,780
You think I don't
deserve to be here.

2320
02:45:47,010 --> 02:45:49,300
I am taking advantage
of my dad being a general!

2321
02:45:49,630 --> 02:45:52,320
I've cleared every obstacle
of the special forces...

2322
02:45:52,440 --> 02:45:54,050
...and that too with
flying colours, Tank.

2323
02:45:54,120 --> 02:45:56,040
Not my dad.
You get it?

2324
02:45:59,910 --> 02:46:01,620
F*****g lunatic.

2325
02:46:11,280 --> 02:46:14,470
- Sir, what does this mean?
- Lack of initiative.

2326
02:46:14,550 --> 02:46:16,810
Sir, why? Because I am a
soldier and not an officer...

2327
02:46:16,890 --> 02:46:19,030
...you think I can't
take good decision.

2328
02:46:19,110 --> 02:46:20,130
This is not true, Tej.

2329
02:46:20,310 --> 02:46:22,310
And before saying anything
to me look at your report.

2330
02:46:22,400 --> 02:46:24,730
What is this?
"Capt. Manit is not a team player!"

2331
02:46:24,970 --> 02:46:26,430
- Really, Tej?
- Yes, sir.

2332
02:46:26,520 --> 02:46:28,930
You do what you think is right.
You don't listen to anyone.

2333
02:46:28,990 --> 02:46:31,040
I'm not the only one who says this.
Everyone says this.

2334
02:46:31,120 --> 02:46:32,490
Actually, you are right.

2335
02:46:32,920 --> 02:46:35,010
I shouldn't have written
lack of initiative.

2336
02:46:35,440 --> 02:46:37,430
I should have written careless.

2337
02:46:37,710 --> 02:46:41,830
As far as I remember you lost
your magazine during Dozakh.

2338
02:46:41,930 --> 02:46:45,300
But sir, you told me to hide
this from Capt. Shikha.

2339
02:46:45,380 --> 02:46:47,510
- F*****g idiot.
- Boys...

2340
02:46:47,600 --> 02:46:50,620
Relax. This is the Indian army.
We have a decorum here.

2341
02:46:53,580 --> 02:46:55,610
Colonel Sathe is testing us.

2342
02:46:55,850 --> 02:46:57,470
[Tank] 'So that we react this way.'

2343
02:46:57,830 --> 02:46:59,450
Please don't fall for it.

2344
02:47:00,560 --> 02:47:03,850
Not Colonel Sathe. Lt. Colonel
Imtiyaz Hussain. He has done it.

2345
02:47:04,020 --> 02:47:05,470
And this is not the last time.

2346
02:47:05,770 --> 02:47:08,480
I have a feeling, he will
try to trick us like this again.

2347
02:47:08,670 --> 02:47:12,750
Unbelievable, Imtiyaz. You leaked
the psychological profile reports!

2348
02:47:12,930 --> 02:47:15,720
I just gave you the permission
to conduct a class.

2349
02:47:15,810 --> 02:47:18,170
- And I took them to task.
- Imtiyaz.

2350
02:47:18,700 --> 02:47:20,620
This is completely unacceptable.

2351
02:47:20,700 --> 02:47:22,420
This could create
a rift amongst them.

2352
02:47:22,500 --> 02:47:25,400
We are trying to unite them
and not separate.

2353
02:47:25,500 --> 02:47:27,660
Sir, the team
which breaks so easily...

2354
02:47:27,820 --> 02:47:29,700
...is not worthy to be
in the special forces.

2355
02:47:30,170 --> 02:47:30,890
What do you mean?

2356
02:47:30,980 --> 02:47:34,370
Only Squad Alpha knows
what happened in Dozakh.

2357
02:47:34,450 --> 02:47:35,800
And sir, my gut feeling says...

2358
02:47:35,880 --> 02:47:38,710
...that even RMO, Aparna does
not have the entire picture.

2359
02:47:41,510 --> 02:47:42,790
Imtiyaz.

2360
02:47:44,610 --> 02:47:47,620
You have my full support
for the investigation.

2361
02:47:47,780 --> 02:47:51,340
But there is a code
of honour in the army.

2362
02:47:52,080 --> 02:47:53,170
Which is sacrosanct...

2363
02:47:53,250 --> 02:47:54,910
...and which is above anything.

2364
02:47:55,220 --> 02:47:56,870
I agree with you, sir.

2365
02:47:57,170 --> 02:47:59,070
But with all due respect...

2366
02:47:59,140 --> 02:48:02,860
...is this code of honour more
important than a lady's honour?

2367
02:48:04,250 --> 02:48:05,730
Sir, something has happened.

2368
02:48:05,830 --> 02:48:08,370
And either the one who sent
the e-mail can tell me this...

2369
02:48:08,450 --> 02:48:10,950
...or Capt. Shikha herself.

2370
02:48:11,240 --> 02:48:14,430
And right now, both...
Both are lying, sir.

2371
02:48:21,940 --> 02:48:26,030
Reports look good.
Your progress is also good.

2372
02:48:26,460 --> 02:48:28,490
I am from Haryana.
It is in my blood.

2373
02:48:30,070 --> 02:48:32,010
Thank you for everything, Aparna.

2374
02:48:34,830 --> 02:48:38,280
Shikha, Colonel Imtiyaz
came here to meet me.

2375
02:48:43,040 --> 02:48:44,370
What did he say?

2376
02:48:45,910 --> 02:48:47,090
He didn't say anything.

2377
02:48:48,570 --> 02:48:51,660
But he had some very
disturbing questions.

2378
02:48:53,280 --> 02:48:54,520
Like.

2379
02:49:25,910 --> 02:49:28,370
-[Shikha] 'May I come in, sir?'
- Yes.

2380
02:49:28,470 --> 02:49:29,280
[Door opening]

2381
02:49:31,620 --> 02:49:33,610
- Sir.
- At ease.

2382
02:49:40,970 --> 02:49:43,130
You are asking questions
about me from everyone, sir.

2383
02:49:43,210 --> 02:49:44,920
So, I thought I myself
should come here, sir.

2384
02:49:48,930 --> 02:49:50,430
I don't play poker, sir.

2385
02:49:50,950 --> 02:49:52,120
I used to play with
catapult when I was a kid...

2386
02:49:52,180 --> 02:49:55,070
...and I am now, a shooter.
I prefer talking to the point, sir.

2387
02:50:00,380 --> 02:50:01,850
Point taken, Capt. Sharma.

2388
02:50:02,570 --> 02:50:05,010
So, why don't you tell me
the truth point-blank?

2389
02:50:05,120 --> 02:50:06,910
The truth is, sir
that I am a Belieber.

2390
02:50:06,980 --> 02:50:08,470
"What do you mean"
is my favourite song.

2391
02:50:08,550 --> 02:50:10,160
Pink has always been
my favourite colour.

2392
02:50:10,260 --> 02:50:11,900
I'm not a virgin.
I'm sexually active.

2393
02:50:11,980 --> 02:50:13,950
I have a steady boyfriend
but I'm not promiscuous.

2394
02:50:14,030 --> 02:50:16,150
And I never got pregnant
till date, sir.

2395
02:50:20,700 --> 02:50:24,280
Well, I am not asking
about all this.

2396
02:50:24,910 --> 02:50:29,330
But okay. Now that we are talking,
why don't you tell me?

2397
02:50:29,760 --> 02:50:32,520
You seem to be very
emotional about...

2398
02:50:32,580 --> 02:50:35,100
What's his name? Shivalik.

2399
02:50:36,020 --> 02:50:38,400
But you didn't even call him
after Dozakh.

2400
02:50:38,880 --> 02:50:41,220
You didn't even tell him
what happened with you.

2401
02:50:44,160 --> 02:50:46,710
I really appreciate the fact
that you worked really hard...

2402
02:50:46,830 --> 02:50:49,190
...to get the records
of my messages and calls.

2403
02:50:49,630 --> 02:50:52,460
But if you think that owing to such
tactics I'll become emotional...

2404
02:50:52,540 --> 02:50:55,770
...and I'll crack,
it's not going to happen, sir.

2405
02:50:57,070 --> 02:50:59,770
Till date I never met a lady
who is not emotional.

2406
02:50:59,870 --> 02:51:02,770
Women are emotional, sir
but they are also smart.

2407
02:51:03,140 --> 02:51:07,600
Like your ex-wife, sir.
Pardon me, sir. But...

2408
02:51:07,690 --> 02:51:09,570
Maybe that is why she left you.

2409
02:51:12,630 --> 02:51:14,280
Military Intelligence, sir.

2410
02:51:15,060 --> 02:51:17,580
Handpicked after
rigorous deep selection.

2411
02:51:20,810 --> 02:51:25,070
What happened, sir? Aren't you
used to intelligent women?

2412
02:51:29,690 --> 02:51:31,470
To be intelligent and to
think others as stupid...

2413
02:51:31,550 --> 02:51:33,580
...are two different things.

2414
02:51:34,300 --> 02:51:37,650
You think I don't know who
leaked the strategy class reports?

2415
02:51:38,690 --> 02:51:40,780
I know you have friends in MI.

2416
02:51:40,990 --> 02:51:44,600
Capt. Sharma, I know that
something has happened with you.

2417
02:51:44,720 --> 02:51:46,790
And you are taking revenge
by leaking the reports.

2418
02:51:48,020 --> 02:51:51,230
But if you tell me, I can help you.

2419
02:51:51,610 --> 02:51:56,340
- I can help you.
- I don't want anyone's help, sir.

2420
02:51:57,090 --> 02:51:59,470
You can carry on
with your investigation.

2421
02:51:59,860 --> 02:52:02,350
The one who sent the e-mail
might tell you something.

2422
02:52:02,460 --> 02:52:04,260
Maybe you sent that e-mail.

2423
02:52:06,090 --> 02:52:07,770
You may leave, Capt. Sharma.

2424
02:52:12,330 --> 02:52:16,420
One thing that I like the
most about Colonel Sathe.

2425
02:52:16,920 --> 02:52:18,530
He loves reverse psychology.

2426
02:52:18,620 --> 02:52:21,000
Red form and blue form
in the psychological tests...

2427
02:52:21,080 --> 02:52:23,310
Blue wire and red wire
in the bomb test...

2428
02:52:23,420 --> 02:52:26,580
Blue means enemies,
red means friends.

2429
02:52:28,840 --> 02:52:31,050
Blue wire was supposed
to be cut, Capt. Sharma.

2430
02:52:31,440 --> 02:52:34,830
But as per everyone's debriefs,
the red wire was cut.

2431
02:52:35,460 --> 02:52:36,620
[Imtiyaz] 'Why?'

2432
02:52:37,370 --> 02:52:39,470
Manit, I have an instinct.

2433
02:52:39,550 --> 02:52:40,850
It's reverse psychology.
Go with the blue.

2434
02:52:40,930 --> 02:52:42,490
- What about logic?
- Manit, blue.

2435
02:52:42,570 --> 02:52:44,430
- Red.
- Blue. - Red!

2436
02:52:47,460 --> 02:52:48,640
[All] 'Raju...'

2437
02:52:48,720 --> 02:52:50,260
Raju, here...
Back...

2438
02:52:50,340 --> 02:52:51,920
Tank, back.
Back...

2439
02:52:52,000 --> 02:52:53,490
Manit, back.
Manit, back.

2440
02:52:55,020 --> 02:52:56,110
Capt. Shikha.

2441
02:52:56,370 --> 02:52:57,330
Come, let's play a game.

2442
02:52:57,610 --> 02:52:58,770
I don't play games, dude.

2443
02:52:58,850 --> 02:52:59,870
I am a sportsman.

2444
02:53:00,350 --> 02:53:03,600
Well, I must appreciate your
sportsman spirit, Capt. Manit.

2445
02:53:05,660 --> 02:53:06,720
What do you mean?

2446
02:53:06,800 --> 02:53:08,550
Which wire did you cut
during bomb defusal?

2447
02:53:08,630 --> 02:53:09,670
Red or blue?

2448
02:53:11,600 --> 02:53:13,570
Capt. Manit, red or blue?

2449
02:53:16,300 --> 02:53:18,220
Red or blue?

2450
02:53:21,100 --> 02:53:21,930
Blue.

2451
02:53:24,910 --> 02:53:27,000
You told us that
you cut the red wire.

2452
02:53:27,980 --> 02:53:29,300
Why did you lie to everyone?

2453
02:53:30,780 --> 02:53:32,030
Is this your team spirit?

2454
02:53:32,410 --> 02:53:34,580
You didn't want to give up
in front of a girl.

2455
02:53:36,750 --> 02:53:38,730
Your male ego couldn't handle this.

2456
02:53:38,810 --> 02:53:41,160
Sir, you said that
you cut the red wire.

2457
02:53:41,310 --> 02:53:42,390
[Tank] Red wire?

2458
02:53:43,280 --> 02:53:45,270
Even in our task, blue
was the right wire.

2459
02:53:47,660 --> 02:53:48,870
As my 2IC...

2460
02:53:49,080 --> 02:53:52,290
...you must have a very good
reason to tell a lie like this.

2461
02:53:52,640 --> 02:53:54,460
Please enlighten us.
We are all waiting.

2462
02:53:57,900 --> 02:53:59,620
- I lied for the team.
- Sorry?

2463
02:54:00,390 --> 02:54:03,320
- For the team?
- With all due respect.

2464
02:54:03,640 --> 02:54:05,750
You took a wrong decision first.

2465
02:54:05,890 --> 02:54:07,610
Because of which
we lost a lot of time.

2466
02:54:07,820 --> 02:54:09,250
And we didn't even
get our supplies.

2467
02:54:10,430 --> 02:54:11,590
So, after a point I felt...

2468
02:54:11,670 --> 02:54:13,930
...Rohan should be our
team leader instead of you.

2469
02:54:16,330 --> 02:54:18,340
He was the best amongst us,
Capt. Shikha.

2470
02:54:19,490 --> 02:54:20,910
Are you the commandant here?

2471
02:54:22,140 --> 02:54:25,880
Will you decide who should
be the leader of which team?

2472
02:54:26,740 --> 02:54:29,270
I was not the only one.
We all thought so.

2473
02:54:30,340 --> 02:54:31,340
Even Bilal.

2474
02:54:34,180 --> 02:54:36,630
Anyway, what difference
does it make...

2475
02:54:36,710 --> 02:54:37,590
...if I cut the red wire or blue?

2476
02:54:38,520 --> 02:54:40,670
The fact is we were all safe.

2477
02:54:41,470 --> 02:54:43,120
Isn't that what matters?
What say, guys?

2478
02:54:43,400 --> 02:54:45,560
Hey. Good that you
were not in our team.

2479
02:54:45,760 --> 02:54:47,490
She is asking you nicely.

2480
02:54:47,620 --> 02:54:50,400
Whereas the Squad Bravo
would've done your kambal parade.

2481
02:54:52,610 --> 02:54:53,610
You are safe.

2482
02:54:56,940 --> 02:55:00,000
If you want, you can
complain to Colonel Sathe.

2483
02:55:01,560 --> 02:55:02,830
Vishnu, even you
were with him, right?

2484
02:55:05,080 --> 02:55:06,570
B*******d, even you
didn't tell the truth.

2485
02:55:22,510 --> 02:55:23,430
Shikha.

2486
02:55:24,290 --> 02:55:25,410
Shikha, stop please.

2487
02:55:26,990 --> 02:55:28,200
Shikha, listen to me.
Shikha.

2488
02:55:28,840 --> 02:55:30,070
Shame on you, man.

2489
02:55:30,310 --> 02:55:31,570
Why did you do this to me?

2490
02:55:32,490 --> 02:55:34,230
I was wrong during
the navigation exercise.

2491
02:55:34,310 --> 02:55:35,120
You were right.

2492
02:55:35,200 --> 02:55:37,220
But seriously.
This!

2493
02:55:37,760 --> 02:55:39,470
How do you look at yourself
in the mirror?

2494
02:55:39,890 --> 02:55:41,810
- I'm really sorry, Shikha.
- It's too late.

2495
02:55:42,570 --> 02:55:45,440
Such a big lie!
Why?

2496
02:55:46,740 --> 02:55:47,920
Shikha, I'm sorry.

2497
02:55:49,190 --> 02:55:51,500
And believe me, it's not about you.

