2747
03:08:59,730 --> 03:09:02,130
Then when the mishap
of navigation happened...

2748
03:09:02,270 --> 03:09:04,960
...I felt Rohan is better
suited for the job.

2749
03:09:05,190 --> 03:09:07,870
It means, though
you were friends...

2750
03:09:07,950 --> 03:09:09,600
...you were not happy that Shikha
was made the team leader.

2751
03:09:10,060 --> 03:09:10,780
Why?

2752
03:09:10,860 --> 03:09:13,540
- Sir, I just said...
- Is it because she is a woman?

2753
03:09:13,770 --> 03:09:14,770
No.

2754
03:09:14,850 --> 03:09:15,930
No, sir.
Not at all.

2755
03:09:16,640 --> 03:09:19,080
I genuinely felt that Rohan
is better suited for the job.

2756
03:09:19,350 --> 03:09:20,950
It means that Shikha
is not a good leader.

2757
03:09:21,100 --> 03:09:22,540
Sir, I didn't say that.

2758
03:09:22,990 --> 03:09:24,430
Shikha is really good.

2759
03:09:24,570 --> 03:09:27,440
But there are a few people in
Squad Alpha who are more deserving.

2760
03:09:27,520 --> 03:09:28,410
Like who?

2761
03:09:29,240 --> 03:09:30,450
Like...

2762
03:09:30,670 --> 03:09:31,680
Like Manit.

2763
03:09:31,990 --> 03:09:33,840
Rohan or perhaps me.

2764
03:09:33,920 --> 03:09:36,070
It means everyone except Shikha.

2765
03:09:36,150 --> 03:09:37,450
Sir, I didn't say that.

2766
03:09:37,890 --> 03:09:39,590
Shikha is good.
In fact very good.

2767
03:09:39,670 --> 03:09:40,610
Very good for a woman.

2768
03:09:40,950 --> 03:09:41,980
This is what you mean to say,
right?

2769
03:09:42,300 --> 03:09:43,690
- No, sir.
- You know, Capt. Bilal...

2770
03:09:44,400 --> 03:09:46,830
Shikha was your friend.
First lady commando.

2771
03:09:47,130 --> 03:09:49,110
Exemplary in all
her courses so far...

2772
03:09:49,190 --> 03:09:51,310
...yet you couldn't
trust her 100 percent.

2773
03:09:51,390 --> 03:09:55,210
When Manit cut the blue wire
instead of red and lied...

2774
03:09:55,290 --> 03:09:57,420
...you supported him.
All of you supported him.

2775
03:09:58,400 --> 03:10:03,220
Just because you couldn't accept
a lady officer as a team leader.

2776
03:10:03,660 --> 03:10:05,410
- This is not true.
- Then you fell unconscious...

2777
03:10:05,490 --> 03:10:08,140
...but you and every member
of Squad Alpha...

2778
03:10:08,220 --> 03:10:09,970
...wrote exactly the same debriefs.

2779
03:10:10,410 --> 03:10:11,310
Word by word.

2780
03:10:12,680 --> 03:10:13,660
What is all this?

2781
03:10:14,420 --> 03:10:16,360
Some kind of a bro code
in your boys club.

2782
03:10:16,470 --> 03:10:18,020
Except that because of
this Capt. Sharma...

2783
03:10:18,100 --> 03:10:20,140
...whom you call your friend...

2784
03:10:20,220 --> 03:10:21,570
...got into trouble.

2785
03:10:21,880 --> 03:10:23,290
What type of friendship
is this, Capt. Bilal...

2786
03:10:23,420 --> 03:10:25,580
...that you didn't even have
the balls to look her in the eye...

2787
03:10:25,660 --> 03:10:27,330
...and say goodbye
to her as you left?

2788
03:10:28,780 --> 03:10:29,680
Fine.

2789
03:10:30,620 --> 03:10:32,450
You all are saying
that nothing happened.

2790
03:10:32,530 --> 03:10:34,590
So, I'll also write in my report
that nothing happened.

2791
03:10:35,820 --> 03:10:38,170
Shikha is nothing
but a manipulative liar.

2792
03:10:38,380 --> 03:10:39,790
And she shouldn't pass this course.

2793
03:10:39,870 --> 03:10:40,990
Sir, no matter how Shikha is...

2794
03:10:41,080 --> 03:10:42,330
...she is not manipulative.

2795
03:10:44,500 --> 03:10:46,590
You are trying to save your friend.

2796
03:10:50,120 --> 03:10:52,040
I wish I could protect her, sir.

2797
03:10:53,360 --> 03:10:54,360
I wish.

2798
03:10:55,420 --> 03:10:57,920
But trust me, sir.
Shikha is a strong girl.

2799
03:10:58,000 --> 03:10:59,290
She can protect herself.

2800
03:11:00,300 --> 03:11:01,840
I am not protecting her now.

2801
03:11:04,380 --> 03:11:05,760
Whom are you protecting then?

2802
03:11:07,400 --> 03:11:10,010
[Shikha] 'Bilal, are you okay?
Bilal.'

2803
03:11:15,610 --> 03:11:19,540
[Screams]

2804
03:11:21,480 --> 03:11:22,550
[Man2] 'Alpha1, come in.'

2805
03:11:29,230 --> 03:11:34,040
So, you won't tell me anything.
Fine.

2806
03:11:42,290 --> 03:11:45,570
Capt. Sharma, I don't
want to hurt you.

2807
03:11:46,080 --> 03:11:47,060
Let's keep it civil.

2808
03:11:47,760 --> 03:11:49,450
But I don't wish to do so.

2809
03:12:02,860 --> 03:12:03,870
What happened?

2810
03:12:04,360 --> 03:12:06,190
Being a Rajput, why
have you suddenly lost your valour?

2811
03:12:14,240 --> 03:12:15,490
Stealth and surprise.

2812
03:12:15,780 --> 03:12:17,590
First lesson of the special forces.

2813
03:12:18,490 --> 03:12:19,440
[Pained scream]

2814
03:12:26,700 --> 03:12:28,900
Come on, Rohan.
One more.

2815
03:12:30,300 --> 03:12:31,470
You know I can take it.

2816
03:12:42,770 --> 03:12:43,720
Stop!

2817
03:12:44,910 --> 03:12:46,010
Very good, Capt. Sharma.

2818
03:12:51,390 --> 03:12:52,150
Are you okay?

2819
03:12:52,230 --> 03:12:54,670
Are you fine, Capt. Rohan?
Are you okay?

2820
03:13:56,780 --> 03:13:58,310
I know what the truth is.

2821
03:13:59,050 --> 03:14:01,580
And I also know
that you know the truth.

2822
03:14:01,860 --> 03:14:02,990
Sir, it's not what you think.

2823
03:14:03,070 --> 03:14:04,320
It's exactly what I think.

2824
03:14:04,420 --> 03:14:07,020
- No, sir.. It's...
- It is exactly what I think.

2825
03:14:08,230 --> 03:14:11,020
I just met your dearest
friend, Capt. Bilal.

2826
03:14:12,070 --> 03:14:14,230
- Sir, he is an overemotional...
- Relax, Capt. Rathore.

2827
03:14:15,290 --> 03:14:16,630
Capt. Bilal didn't say anything.

2828
03:14:18,360 --> 03:14:21,000
What are you doing here
if Capt. Bilal didn't say anything?

2829
03:14:22,800 --> 03:14:23,720
You invited me here.

2830
03:14:23,800 --> 03:14:25,730
And now you are asking me
what I am doing here!

2831
03:14:26,840 --> 03:14:29,830
I know that you had sent that
anonymous mail, Capt. Rathore.

2832
03:14:31,690 --> 03:14:35,300
Right cyber cafe, right time,
right mail, right recipient...

2833
03:14:36,580 --> 03:14:38,070
But you made one mistake.

2834
03:14:41,110 --> 03:14:42,350
He was wearing a muffler.

2835
03:14:42,450 --> 03:14:44,130
- Just...
- Muffler?

2836
03:14:44,380 --> 03:14:46,800
Yes, sir. It was this colour.
Red colour.

2837
03:14:48,720 --> 03:14:51,500
Your daughter must have gifted
this bright pink muffler to you.

2838
03:14:52,580 --> 03:14:53,620
Am I right?

2839
03:14:55,620 --> 03:14:56,680
Frankly, Capt. Rathore...

2840
03:14:56,760 --> 03:14:59,510
...till 2 hours ago, you were
accused number 1 for me.

2841
03:15:00,040 --> 03:15:02,650
But your Krav Maga
exercise saved you.

2842
03:15:04,010 --> 03:15:05,540
[Imtiyaz] 'Shikha's injuries
are on the left side.'

2843
03:15:06,130 --> 03:15:07,160
[Imtiyaz] 'But you are a leftie.'

2844
03:15:07,640 --> 03:15:10,630
A right-handed person
has assaulted Shikha.

2845
03:15:12,010 --> 03:15:13,810
I think it's time now,
Capt. Rathore...

2846
03:15:14,470 --> 03:15:17,890
...that you tell me
what happened that day.

2847
03:15:26,650 --> 03:15:27,930
36 hours.

2848
03:15:29,570 --> 03:15:31,450
Keep walking.
[Siren.]

2849
03:15:31,650 --> 03:15:33,280
[Rohan] 'Without food or sleep.'

2850
03:15:34,720 --> 03:15:36,170
- Red.
- Blue. - Red.

2851
03:15:36,550 --> 03:15:38,240
[Rohan] 'Moreover,
we were given sleeping pills.'

2852
03:15:39,080 --> 03:15:40,660
[Rohan] 'Some people were
having hallucinations and...'

2853
03:15:40,750 --> 03:15:42,010
[Rohan] 'Some just
couldn't take it.'

2854
03:15:42,100 --> 03:15:46,900
[Gunshots]

2855
03:15:49,110 --> 03:15:50,340
[Pained scream]

2856
03:15:55,560 --> 03:15:57,210
- Alpha 1, come in.
- Rohan.

2857
03:15:57,500 --> 03:15:59,360
Rohan, where are the targets
coming from?

2858
03:15:59,550 --> 03:16:00,690
They are moving targets.

2859
03:16:00,770 --> 03:16:02,350
I guess, we've been surrounded.

2860
03:16:03,160 --> 03:16:04,170
Bilal, are you okay?

2861
03:16:05,060 --> 03:16:06,160
Bilal.

2862
03:16:06,770 --> 03:16:08,440
Bro, shall we move ahead?

2863
03:16:09,180 --> 03:16:10,650
We are losing precious time, man.

2864
03:16:15,140 --> 03:16:17,220
Bilal...

2865
03:16:17,350 --> 03:16:18,380
Capt. Sharma.

2866
03:16:19,010 --> 03:16:21,480
Bilal is a tough cookie.
He will survive this.

2867
03:16:21,610 --> 03:16:24,570
But if we stay here, we'll
never reach the end point.

2868
03:16:24,650 --> 03:16:26,590
Capt. Rohan, take the
defensive position.

2869
03:16:26,730 --> 03:16:28,770
We can't leave Bilal behind.

2870
03:16:28,840 --> 03:16:30,960
Would you say the same
if this was a real war?

2871
03:16:31,510 --> 03:16:33,300
You can win the war
with logic, Capt. Sharma...

2872
03:16:33,390 --> 03:16:34,470
...and not with emotions.

2873
03:16:34,670 --> 03:16:36,340
Capt. Manit, would you
have said the same thing...

2874
03:16:36,420 --> 03:16:37,720
...if you were in Bilal's place?

2875
03:16:38,770 --> 03:16:40,630
Rohan, do as I say?
Take the defensive position.

2876
03:16:45,280 --> 03:16:46,550
[Gunshots]

2877
03:16:46,630 --> 03:16:47,820
[Screams]

2878
03:16:50,970 --> 03:16:53,140
Bilal...
Bilal, you okay?

2879
03:16:53,310 --> 03:16:54,630
Bilal, are you hit?
Bilal.

2880
03:16:56,090 --> 03:16:58,830
Tej Bahadur, is Vishnu all right?

2881
03:16:58,930 --> 03:17:00,080
No, sir.

2882
03:17:01,540 --> 03:17:04,070
Tej, is there firing in the
direction that we just came in?

2883
03:17:05,570 --> 03:17:07,420
No, sir.
This way is clear.

2884
03:17:08,070 --> 03:17:10,280
Tej, you'll move back
along with Vishnu.

2885
03:17:10,560 --> 03:17:12,680
- We will give you cover. Copy?
- Yes, sir.

2886
03:17:12,740 --> 03:17:13,880
[Gunshots]

2887
03:17:14,750 --> 03:17:15,830
Vishnu.

2888
03:17:21,570 --> 03:17:22,280
Come on.

2889
03:17:24,290 --> 03:17:26,360
Capt. Sharma, are you
suggesting us to retreat?

2890
03:17:26,640 --> 03:17:28,150
If you and Rohan give me cover...

2891
03:17:28,240 --> 03:17:30,620
...Tej and I will go in the middle
and establish the perimeter.

2892
03:17:30,800 --> 03:17:32,440
We need these points, Capt. Sharma.

2893
03:17:32,520 --> 03:17:34,260
We have to finish
this exercise, damn it.

2894
03:17:34,360 --> 03:17:35,650
I will not risk the
lives of my men...

2895
03:17:35,730 --> 03:17:37,040
...to complete this exercise,
Manit.

2896
03:17:38,340 --> 03:17:39,870
[Gunshots]

2897
03:17:43,140 --> 03:17:44,590
You are a f*****g coward.

2898
03:17:46,870 --> 03:17:48,910
S***a, you are putting up
a drama saying...

2899
03:17:48,990 --> 03:17:50,440
..."I'll not risk
the lives of my men"...

2900
03:17:50,520 --> 03:17:51,660
in order to hide your cowardice.

2901
03:17:53,500 --> 03:17:55,350
Rats are the ones
who hide, Capt. Sharma.

2902
03:17:55,970 --> 03:17:56,850
Men don't hide.

2903
03:17:57,730 --> 03:17:59,590
Men fight in war and
that too, only to win.

2904
03:17:59,650 --> 03:18:00,790
Hey, Amitabh Bachchan.

2905
03:18:01,560 --> 03:18:03,100
We will win the war
only if we stay alive.

2906
03:18:03,630 --> 03:18:05,960
This is not a simulation exercise.
These bullets are real.

2907
03:18:06,580 --> 03:18:08,290
We just have one way
and that is to move back.

2908
03:18:08,630 --> 03:18:09,780
We have to retreat.

2909
03:18:10,520 --> 03:18:12,970
What do we do? Do you
want us to behave like girls?

2910
03:18:14,510 --> 03:18:15,800
How dare you, Manit!

2911
03:18:17,200 --> 03:18:19,180
Do you have any doubt about
who is in command here?

2912
03:18:20,870 --> 03:18:23,540
- Are you?
- Yes, I am.

2913
03:18:27,990 --> 03:18:30,570
1950 Army Act, Section 46.

2914
03:18:30,870 --> 03:18:33,820
Misconduct, desertion,
disobedience, use of force.

2915
03:18:34,610 --> 03:18:36,850
You can get
court-martialled for this.

2916
03:18:38,320 --> 03:18:41,490
I won't put my squad at risk...

2917
03:18:41,570 --> 03:18:43,780
...because of your machismo
and ego trip, Manit.

2918
03:18:44,790 --> 03:18:48,040
And if I'll have to shoot you
in order to save my squad...

2919
03:18:48,750 --> 03:18:50,410
...I will fire.

2920
03:18:52,530 --> 03:18:55,100
We have to retreat.
And that is final.

2921
03:18:56,370 --> 03:18:57,700
Did you understand?

2922
03:19:01,330 --> 03:19:02,690
[Screams]

2923
03:19:04,860 --> 03:19:06,650
What the f**k are you doing,
Manit?

2924
03:19:06,760 --> 03:19:09,670
[Screams]

2925
03:19:15,440 --> 03:19:18,970
Sir, that was the moment
which I'll regret my entire life.

2926
03:19:21,160 --> 03:19:23,390
Because I was the only one
who could have intervened.

2927
03:19:24,490 --> 03:19:27,070
But I didn't.
I chose the wrong side.

2928
03:19:28,090 --> 03:19:29,190
But believe me, sir.

2929
03:19:29,300 --> 03:19:31,510
I had no idea what
would happen next.

2930
03:19:31,850 --> 03:19:36,650
[Screams]

2931
03:19:47,780 --> 03:19:49,300
You f*****g b***h!

2932
03:19:51,810 --> 03:19:52,910
Are you done now, s***i?

2933
03:19:52,970 --> 03:19:55,400
Now you see, I'll put
you back in your place.

2934
03:20:01,830 --> 03:20:04,260
Manit, what are you doing?

2935
03:20:06,820 --> 03:20:07,850
Manit!

2936
03:20:08,740 --> 03:20:09,830
Manit!

2937
03:20:10,220 --> 03:20:11,410
Manit!

2938
03:20:11,490 --> 03:20:13,060
[Cough and gasping]

2939
03:20:15,100 --> 03:20:18,510
[Unbuckle belt]

2940
03:20:19,510 --> 03:20:20,770
[Manit]

2941
03:20:23,680 --> 03:20:26,070
Stop it.
Manit!

2942
03:20:33,150 --> 03:20:36,250
- Manit!
- Shut up!

2943
03:20:39,390 --> 03:20:42,220
[Cries]

2944
03:21:01,040 --> 03:21:05,830
[Cries]

2945
03:21:07,600 --> 03:21:08,790
[Pained scream]

2946
03:21:19,460 --> 03:21:20,810
Manit.
B*******d.

2947
03:21:21,710 --> 03:21:23,230
You f*****g b*****d.

2948
03:21:23,550 --> 03:21:25,120
Shikha.
Capt. Sharma.

2949
03:21:25,470 --> 03:21:26,530
Capt. Sharma, are you okay?

2950
03:21:26,940 --> 03:21:28,220
[Gunshots]

2951
03:21:29,020 --> 03:21:30,520
Sharma.

2952
03:21:42,110 --> 03:21:43,160
Capt. Sharma.

2953
03:21:45,830 --> 03:21:47,600
F*****g a*****e.
What were you doing?

2954
03:21:48,130 --> 03:21:50,220
Shikha, everything is fine.
Shikha, you are fine.

2955
03:21:50,330 --> 03:21:52,250
Shikha, look at me.
Shikha, you are fine.

2956
03:21:52,330 --> 03:21:53,340
Rohan...

2957
03:21:53,510 --> 03:21:54,810
[Buttstroke]

2958
03:21:56,010 --> 03:21:57,750
Manit, s***e.
B*******d.

2959
03:21:58,220 --> 03:21:59,610
What the hell are you doing?

2960
03:21:59,690 --> 03:22:02,140
Rohan.
Rohan, try to understand.

2961
03:22:02,370 --> 03:22:03,520
If she were conscious...

2962
03:22:03,610 --> 03:22:05,550
...we both would have been
charged with disobedience.

2963
03:22:05,690 --> 03:22:07,130
And we would've never become SFs.

2964
03:22:07,600 --> 03:22:08,750
[Coughs]

2965
03:22:09,630 --> 03:22:11,380
Now, it will be her
words against ours.

2966
03:22:12,060 --> 03:22:13,150
And no witness.

2967
03:22:14,520 --> 03:22:16,100
[Coughs]

2968
03:22:17,390 --> 03:22:19,520
We have given our blood and
sweat to reach this place.

2969
03:22:19,720 --> 03:22:21,120
We cannot let this go.

2970
03:22:23,200 --> 03:22:25,050
[Coughs]

2971
03:22:28,720 --> 03:22:32,450
After that the firing stopped
but we had lost radio contact.

2972
03:22:35,730 --> 03:22:39,330
Maybe even Mr. Bhatti had found
out that there is something wrong.

2973
03:22:52,190 --> 03:22:53,320
She slipped.

2974
03:22:55,230 --> 03:22:56,360
She hit her head.

2975
03:23:27,670 --> 03:23:29,430
Capt. Rathore, I'm not
able to understand...

2976
03:23:29,510 --> 03:23:33,240
...why you didn't lodge an official
complaint with Colonel Sathe.

2977
03:23:34,440 --> 03:23:35,870
Because it wasn't so simple, sir.

2978
03:23:37,660 --> 03:23:40,260
Bilal saw me with Shikha
and not Manit.

2979
03:23:41,120 --> 03:23:42,780
Manit would have blamed me and...

2980
03:23:43,490 --> 03:23:45,330
It would have been just
his word against mine.

2981
03:23:46,540 --> 03:23:47,900
And I thought Shikha would come...

2982
03:23:47,980 --> 03:23:49,740
...and complain against
Manit to Colonel Sathe.

2983
03:23:50,180 --> 03:23:51,450
But she didn't say anything, sir.

2984
03:23:52,890 --> 03:23:55,730
When did you think about
writing this anonymous mail?

2985
03:23:57,910 --> 03:23:59,960
You are not troubling mom, right?

2986
03:24:00,120 --> 03:24:00,910
-[Arshi] No.
-[Rohan] 'I spoke to my daughter'

2987
03:24:00,990 --> 03:24:02,200
[Rohan] 'in the evening.'
Good girl.

2988
03:24:02,690 --> 03:24:06,750
'Dad, I want to wear
the army uniform just like you.'

2989
03:24:14,660 --> 03:24:16,650
Then I went to the military
hospital to meet Shikha.

2990
03:24:17,810 --> 03:24:19,390
I couldn't see
the state she was in.

2991
03:24:21,070 --> 03:24:22,360
I couldn't hold it, sir.

2992
03:24:23,000 --> 03:24:24,220
I had to do something.

2993
03:24:28,590 --> 03:24:31,520
I couldn't see injustice
being done to Shikha, sir.

2994
03:24:32,520 --> 03:24:34,160
Sir, she is also a fellow officer.

2995
03:24:35,860 --> 03:24:37,120
She is also my course mate.

2996
03:24:39,110 --> 03:24:42,260
Bilal was Shikha's
as well as my friend.

2997
03:24:43,470 --> 03:24:45,810
Yet he chose me.
He remain quiet.

2998
03:24:54,930 --> 03:24:59,730
[Footsteps]

2999
03:25:27,600 --> 03:25:28,620
So, officers.

3000
03:25:28,970 --> 03:25:31,410
It's time for the two last
exercises of the course.

3001
03:25:32,130 --> 03:25:33,470
Which means the last opportunity...

3002
03:25:33,540 --> 03:25:36,250
...to increase your rankings
on the leadership board.

3003
03:25:36,970 --> 03:25:38,020
So far the rankings are...

3004
03:25:38,100 --> 03:25:39,710
...Capt. Surjewala at number 5.

3005
03:25:39,790 --> 03:25:41,160
Capt. Tank at number 4.

3006
03:25:41,240 --> 03:25:42,530
Capt. Rohan, number 3.

3007
03:25:42,650 --> 03:25:44,030
Capt. Shikha at number 2.

3008
03:25:44,660 --> 03:25:46,870
And Capt. Manit is at number 1.

3009
03:25:50,010 --> 03:25:51,500
10 shots in 90 seconds.

3010
03:25:51,880 --> 03:25:54,880
Five shots from assault rifle
and five shots from pistol.

3011
03:25:55,050 --> 03:25:56,680
The target will be moving
in the last shot.

3012
03:25:58,270 --> 03:25:59,660
Two fans will be placed
on both the sides.

3013
03:26:00,490 --> 03:26:02,360
The speed of air will
be 10 miles per hour.

3014
